title: jackie's cookies
directions: Mix butter, flour, baking powder and salt by hand like pie crust.
Beat eggs; add milk, vanilla, sugar and soda.
Mix all together, then add flour to mixture.
Chill dough (I mix it up the night before and then bake the next day).
Roll out and cut.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting while warm.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in Pyrex dish.
Place in refrigerator until jello is set.

title: dessert crust
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook Beets until tender.
Peel Beets.
Drain Beets and keep the Beet Water.
Combine the Ingredients and pour the mixture over the sliced beets; bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: angels delight salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup; add to Jell-O.
Let thicken slightly.
Drain and chop maraschino cherries.
When Jell-O has started to thicken, add pineapple, cherries and cheese; fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate and congeal.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook onion, garlic, oregano and tomato sauce in microwave until tender.
Add cooked meat and noodles.
Put in sprayed casserole dish.
Put cheese around top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chocolate-covered pretzels
directions: Combine chocolate and shortening in top of double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts, stirring occasionally.
Remove double boiler from heat, leaving chocolate mixture over hot water.
Dip each pretzel in chocolate; allow excess to drain.
Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheets.
Chill until firm.
Arrange between layer of wax paper in an airtight container.
Store in a cool place.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix butter, sugars, syrup, salt and vanilla together.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from fire.
Add baking soda.
Mix popcorn, pecans and butter in a bowl. Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together green beans, onion, mushroom soup and soup can filled with milk, 1/4 can Durkee dried onions, 2/3 cup Cheddar cheese.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: the kind that would be missed?

title: cheese cake
directions: Spread bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan with butter; dust sides with crumbs.
Force cottage cheese through a fine mesh sieve into a large mixing bowl; add cream cheese.
Beat with high speed of electric mixer until well blended and creamy.
Beating at high speed, gradually blend in sugar, then add eggs.
Reduce speed to low.
Add cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Add melted butter and sour cream.
Blend at low speed. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a slow (325°) oven until firm around edges, about 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Turn off oven; let cake stand in oven with door closed for 2 hours.
Remove from oven and cool completely on wire rack.
Chill.
Remove sides of pan. Makes about 12 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, except Raisin Bran, in very large bowl. Add beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add butter or applesauce.
Mix well again.
Let set for several hours before baking first time.

title: queens apples
directions: Melt caramels in half and half in top of double boiler or over low heat, stirring constantly until creamy.
Put apples into bowls and top with caramel sauce and nuts.
Serve warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sponge gingerbread
directions: Mix in order given, add water last.
Place in 5 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: corn n' cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; add water, sugar and salt to drippings and bring to boil.
Add cabbage and corn.
Cook quickly until tender, about 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Garnish with crisp bacon.
Serves 6.

title: algi ole (oil and garlic)
directions: Heat oil and garlic in a medium saucepan until slightly browned.
Add chopped tomatoes and basil.
Simmer on medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bobbie's punch
directions: Use 2 cups of the water to make tea.
In large container thoroughly mix tea, frozen orange juice, Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add remaining water and stir.
When ready to serve, pour over ice in large bowl.
Add ginger ale and stir.

title: cayenned corn
directions: Cut corn off cob.
Melt butter in skillet and add corn, garlic, cayenne and salt.
Cook for a few minutes over medium heat.
Add milk and cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Will serve 4.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger or Italian sausage; drain and set aside.
In saucepan, heat spaghetti sauce and cottage cheese.
Add meat. When warmed, layer in a 9 x 14-inch dish half of the sauce, all of the noodles and shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Add the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 325° to 350° for about 45 minutes.
Let rest for several minutes after baking and serve.

title: italian-style seafood creole
directions: Cook eggplant, zucchini, mushrooms, onion, pepper and celery in hot oil until tender.
Add undrained tomatoes, wine, soy and the seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and clams.
Simmer 8 minutes.
Serve in bowls plain, with garlic bread or cooked rice, if desired.

title: fast and easy appetizers
directions: You will also need wooden toothpicks.*

title: mile high lemon pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
In saucepan, blend egg yolks, 1 cup sugar, gelatin, water, lemon peel, juice and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture boils.
Place pan in bowl of ice and water; chill in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy.
Beat in 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; continue beating until stiff and glossy. Do not underbeat.
Fold in lemon mixture; pile into pie shell. Chill several hours until set.

title: milky way wonder cake
directions: Melt bars and 1/2 cup butter in pan over low heat.
Cream remaining butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Beat well.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted candy.
Mix.
Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in a tube pan at 350°.

title: christmas cutouts
directions: Cream Criso, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and then rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion, chilies and garlic in oil until soft.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.
I add some cut up chicken breast when I make it.
Precook the breast first.
When serving, put shredded Cheddar cheese and tortilla strips or chips in bowl and add soup.
Sprinkle cilantro chopped up on top.

title: mom's truffles
directions: Bake cake according to package in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Let cake cool.
Make 8 slices in cake; drizzle Amaretto over slices.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice cake into small squares.
In a large bowl, layer ingredients as so:
cake, Hershey's syrup, Cool Whip and Skor bars (crushed).
Repeat layers.
Enjoy!

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine in a large bowl all ingredients.
Mix all together and chill.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Place ice cream on cookie mixture.
Spread around.
Freeze. Combine remaining ingredients in pan over medium heat.
Cook until mixture thickens (5 to 10 minutes).
Cool slightly and spread over ice cream.
Freeze 15 to 30 minutes.
Spread over top of dessert 1 container Cool Whip.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Pour 1 can tomatoes into crock-pot.
Add Velveeta cheese cut into small cubes, ground beef and other can of tomatoes.
Turn crock-pot on high and stir frequently until melted.

title: cornish game hen with white wine
directions: Melt butter and add the next four ingredients.
Baste hens and put into a 350° oven.
Bake for 45 minutes to an hour, basting every 15 minutes.

title: fried and baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken in water with lime juice added; pat dry. Combine salt, pepper, curry powder and flour in bowl; mix well. Dip chicken in mixture to coat.
Brown chicken in hot oil in skillet.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: southwestern chile dip
directions: In a large bowl, stir together Cheddar cheese, mayo, half of olives, green chilies, garlic powder and hot sauce.
Spread into 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate.

title: cheesecake
directions: Melt butter; crush crackers and mix with 2 tablespoons sugar. Press in pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture; add vanilla and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Then mix sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over top and bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Let set in refrigerator for several days, if needed.

title: betty's baked beans
directions: Mix early and cook 7 minutes in microwave.

title: fairy cones
directions: Beat the egg yolks with
the
sugar; add the flour.
Add nuts and spread as thinly
as
possible on greased, flat baking tins. Bake
about
7 minutes.
While
still
warm,
cut
into squares and roll each in the
form
of a cone.
When wanted for use, fill with the sweetened and flavored whipped cream.

title: easy key lime pie(fast, make ahead dessert)
directions: Mix limeade and only 3/4 of canned milk together until mixed well.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze overnight (I cover it with plastic wrap).
Decorate with slices of lime.

title: grandma's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix mayonnaise and Ranch Style dressing mix into cream cheese.
Form into ball and roll in pecans.
(May be frozen.)

title: texas cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Boil water, cocoa and margarine.
Add to flour mixture and mix well. Pour in greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Cook at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry sparkle punch
directions: Put strawberries in blender; blend until pureed.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade until melted.
Add cranberry juice, ice water and strawberry puree.
Pour over ice in a punch bowl.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.

title: watermelon basket
directions: On the upper 1/2 of the melon cut out 2/5's on each side, leaving 1/5 left on top to form a handle of melon.
Scoop out watermelon balls with a melon scoop.
Clean out and smooth inside of basket.
Fill basket with fresh fruit: watermelon balls, cantaloupe balls or cubes, red and green grapes, strawberries, pineapple, apples, oranges, kiwis, nuts and any other fruit in season.
Can throw in some mint leaves if available.
Chill until ready to serve.
Save extra for refilling basket.
Looks pretty, lo-cal and no dishes.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Mix together the ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and grape jam. Add Smokies and simmer. You can double the amount of Smokies to sauce, if desired.

title: crustless chicken pie
directions: Cook fryer in about 3 cups water with the celery, onion, potato and bouillon.
Thicken the broth with 1/4 cup flour.
Add soups, corn, peas and carrots and the margarine and continue to cook until all vegetables are hot.
Pour into a large dish and serve.
No baking required.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix the peanut butter with syrup; can be eaten with a spoon or drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and set in freezer.

title: eggplant skillet dinner
directions: Cook beef, onion and celery until meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and chili powder.
Season eggplant slices with salt and pepper.
Arrange on top of meat sauce.
Cover and simmer until eggplant is tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Process pecans and 1/4 cup sugar until nuts are finely ground.
Add butter, vanilla and salt and blend 1 minute, stopping once to scrape down work load.
Add flour and process until just combined, using 2 or 3 on/off turns.
Do not overprocess.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add rest, except ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and dip ice cream on top of punch.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix. Press in pan.
Cook 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool and fill with ice cream.

title: hot crab piroshki
directions: Prepare pie crust mix for 2-crust pie, substituting 1/2 cup of sour cream for the water called for; set aside.
Combine crab, the remaining 1/2 cup sour cream, onion, egg and hot pepper sauce. Divide pastry in half.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
With a 2 1/2-inch round cutter, cut circles.
Place about 1 teaspoon of filling on half of each circle; moisten edges and fold pastry over filling.
Press edges together with fork.
Repeat with remaining pastry and filling.
Place on baking sheet and brush with a little milk.
Bake in 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be frozen if desired.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and salt. Add sugar and milk. Beat till light and fluffy.

title: slaw
directions: Bring to
a boil sugar, vinegar, salad oil, celery seed and salt.
Mix	1
tablespoon
plus 1 teaspoon sugar with mustard. Add together and pour over vegetables.
Do not open for 3 hours.

title: gourmet spinach
directions: Remove all stems, roots and bruised leaves from spinach.
Wash thoroughly.
When all sand and grit is removed, place in heavy saucepan.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and chop and return to saucepan.
Add cream, butter or margarine, onion, horseradish and a mixture of salt and pepper and stir to blend.
Return to heat; cook until heated thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings; takes 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with margarine by package directions. Crush Ritz crackers. Add cheese to cooked broccoli while hot so cheese melts. Grease 1-quart casserole with margarine and layer broccoli and cracker crumbs. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon candy jelly
directions: Mix.
Bring to boil over hottest fire, stirring constantly. When it comes to boil, add Certo. Stir constantly and boil at full rolling boil for 1/2 minute.
Remove from fire, skim.
Pour into jelly glasses.
Seal with wax.

title: cheese cake
directions: Using large mixing bowl, mix sugar, cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add cornstarch, heavy cream and eggs.
Beat until smooth and well-blended.

title: garden cottage cheese salad
directions: These ingredients can be used according to taste.
Chop all of the vegetables; add 1 teaspoon salt (more or less according to taste).
Mix well.
Ready to serve.
A quick and easy salad and goes with any meal including sandwiches at lunch time.
Also, it is nice for a potluck or carry-in dinner.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately to creamed mixture with applesauce.
Stir in raisins.
Turn batter into greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana-coconut treats
directions: Cut bananas into one-inch thick segments.
Dip into sour cream.
Roll in coconut.
Top with a cherry and place a toothpick through the center.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir thinly sliced zucchini and chopped onion in margarine for 10 minutes.
Stir in chopped parsley or parsley flakes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano leaves. Combine beaten eggs and Mozzarella cheese or Muenster cheese. Stir in zucchini mixture.
Separate dinner rolls into 8 triangles. Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust.

title: janet's chocolate sauce
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar and water.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add chocolate.
Mix well.
Add vanilla; slowly add evaporated milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Cook and stir remaining ingredients, except parsley, in saucepan until hot.
Pour over hot pasta and toss until well coated.
Serve with parsley and additional cheese, if desired.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix in a 9x13x2 pan, the gelatin and boiling water until dissolved.
Add pineapple with juice and blueberry pie filling. Stir and let set in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain well.
Set aside. In bowl, blend soup and flour.
Add sour cream, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold broccoli into soup mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
In small bowl, combine croutons with melted butter, tossing to coat.
Sprinkle over mixture in baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in large iron skillet.
Add all other ingredients, stirring well, then cover and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti noodles (cooked).
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: quick pasta and meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs and 1/2 pack of onion soup.
Roll the mixture into 2-inch meatballs.

title: spoon happenin'
directions: Spread onion dip evenly on lower slice or bagel half.
Lightly sprinkle with hot pepper and apply top slice or bagel half.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Heat salmon juice and add to potatoes
instead of milk. Mix all ingredients.
To shape, use tablespoon.
Dip the spoon full and put in hot grease; fry until
golden brown.
Drain on several thicknesses of paper towels.

title: homemade chocolate pies
directions: Put 1 cup milk and butter in pan; heat.
Then add eggs, flour and cocoa together and cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Let cool.
Top with meringue.
Double for 2 pies.

title: chocolate chip caramel brownies(low-fat)
directions: Heat 1 cup chips, sugar, 1/2 cup evaporated milk, applesauce and margarine in a large heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring until chips are melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in egg substitute.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, vanilla and remaining chips.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Spray with nonstick cooking spray.)

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture until coated.
Put into 12-cup Bundt pan or tube pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar over medium heat until hot.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown and bubbly.
Immediately invert to serving platter. Pull apart to eat.

title: granny's chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour and enough broth to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut into thin strips.
Drop in boiling broth. Add chicken.
Boil about 1 hour or until done.

title: meatballs in curried tomato sauce
directions: Drain 1/2 cup juice from tomatoes and mix with bread.
Add meat, onion, 1 teaspoon seasoned salt, the salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Mix lightly and shape into 24 balls.
Dredge with flour and brown on all sides in hot margarine.
Remove meatballs and pour off fat.

title: lime and pineapple congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat the juice and dissolve the jello in it.
Add crushed pineapple and cottage cheese.
Mix well. Add cool whip and blend.
Fold in pecans.
Sprinkle a few chopped pecans on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
It is best if refrigerated over night.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer.
Put in 3 (5 x 9-inch) loaf pans, that have been greased and floured or sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° about one hour.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out.
Can be wrapped and frozen.
You can add one cup raisins to batter if desired.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Using your favorite meatball recipe, make small meatballs. In a crock-pot add meatballs, ketchup and ginger ale.
Cook at least 2 hours, the longer the better.

title: six spoon salad
directions: Take 1 spoon of raisins, 1 spoon of marshmallows, 1 spoon of peanuts, 1 spoon of coconut and 1 spoon of chopped apple and 1 spoon to stir and eat.
Enjoy a tasty snack.
If you choose, you can mix in Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook noodles
and broccoli by directions on packages and then combine.
Blend
soups with 1 cup milk and mushrooms.
Mix all and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Put mixture on 1/2 of a bun.
Place cheese on top.

title: fruit cake
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, sugar, eggs, milk, cinnamon, cloves and raisins; set aside to cool.
When cool, add flour, nuts, pineapple, cherries and soda.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple, chop eggs and green onions.
Combine chicken, celery, mushrooms, eggs and 2 tablespoons onions.
Stir in mayonnaise, sour cream and salt.
Place pineapple slices on lettuce.
Top each slice of pineapple with chicken salad mix. Garnish with remaining onion and cherry tomatoes.

title: country style ribs
directions: Boil ribs with ginger and enough water to cover ribs for 40 to 45 minutes.
Drain and wash clean.
Combine remaining ingredients for sauce.
Soak ribs in sauce while hot.
Broil over charcoal or in oven.

title: chocolate frosting(two layers)
directions: Blend shortening, egg, cocoa and salt; add sugar alternately with milk and vanilla, mixing until smooth and creamy.
More sugar to thicken or milk to thin can be used.

title: crunchy chicken fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg and milk in shallow dish, add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Place cornflakes crumbs in separate dish.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in crumbs to coat. Place coated chicken on ungreased cookie sheet, drizzle melted butter over chicken and bake 10 minutes, turn sides and bake another 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings

title: min's spanish rice
directions: Cook rice and combine with the ground beef, tomatoes, onion and green pepper.
Season to taste.
Put in a casserole and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients, except noodles and milk.
Cook the noodles until tender.
Add the noodles and the milk.
Bake for 1 hour in a moderate oven.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into heavy skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan with shortening.
Can use glass or metal pans.
Use 13 x 9-inch pans for regular bars, or 9 x 9-inch pans for thicker bars.

title: country-style coleslaw
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix.
Chill, covered, for several hours or overnight.

title: orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the cake mix and the gelatin. Add the water and eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Add the oil and beat for 1 minute.
Pour the batter into the pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain beans, add pickles, eggs, celery and toss lightly.
Add mayonnaise and blend.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce, garnish with egg wedges.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar; put 3/4 of mixture into pie shell.
Heat all of ingredients from milk to vanilla together in a large pot until thickened (stirring all the time). Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar for topping, then put remaining peanut butter mixture on top.
Brown in oven.
Cool in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Fill a large kettle half full with water.
Add all ingredients except milk and cheese.
Simmer until done.
Add milk or cream and cheese.
Do not boil after cheese is added.

title: grandma's cheese cakes
directions: Drop 24 Reynolds Wrap tins into cupcake pans, then drop 1 wafer into each tin.
Mix together all ingredients except filling and drop into tins, about 3/4 full each.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool for about 1/2 hour.
Add filling on top of cakes. Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 24 cups.

title: marshmallow meringue
directions: Cut the marshmallows in small pieces with the kitchen scissors.
Put them, with the milk, in the top of a double boiler; simmer, stirring, about 3 minutes.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Mix everything together but corn flakes and a little butter. Spread into baking dish and put corn flakes and butter mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into ball. Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and ground orange. Sift flour, soda and baking powder, add alternately with sour milk.
Drop from teaspoon on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done, about 10 or 12 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: While sausage is still warm, mix Bisquick and cheese with sausage.
Add a dash of red pepper, rosemary and parsley flakes and continue to mix well.
Roll into bite size balls (small) immediately after mixing.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes until brown. These can be frozen, uncooked, for 2 months.

title: home style custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, lightly beat eggs, salt, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend well.
Spoon in rice and raisins.
Put in ovenproof dish.
Place in pan filled with 1-inch hot water.
Bake uncovered 1 1/4 hours, stirring once after 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar (start with between 1/2 to 3/4 cup powdered sugar and add more as needed). Roll into 1-inch balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple; spread blueberries. Next, sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar.
Next, sprinkle with cake mix. Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over cake mix.
Add pecans; sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour remainder of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cut through layers of Blueberry Crunch with knife after it has baked 25 minutes.

title: jean's jiffy chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Bacon bits may be added.

title: pineapple banana salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple, pour into sauce pan. Add sugar, flour and egg. Whisk together. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens. Set aside to cool.

title: kenny's pineapple pie
directions: Drain juice from crushed pineapple.
Put crushed pineapple on side in bowl.
Blend your cornstarch, sugar and juice only in saucepan.
Cook on low heat until mixture becomes clear, about 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into crushed pineapple bowl.
Stir.
Pour into ready made pie dish.
Cook pie at 450° for 35 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute vegetable in oil.
When tender, add raw rice and stir over moderate heat until grains are dry.
Add spices and vegetable stock (or water).
Cover.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes. Sprinkle in nuts and fruit.
Cook 10 minutes more.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt, then add Crisco.
Using fork or pastry cutter, mix until mixture is similar to coarse meal.
Using fork or wire whip, combine vinegar, egg and water.
Stir into first mixture and combine thoroughly.
Form into large ball and gently pat onto large dinner pate.
Cut into 5 or 6 triangles and then form into small flat rounds.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out on floured surface; fit in pan.
If unfilled, bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place half of the crackers in bottom of a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Add half of the oysters.
Dot generously with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, and nutmeg.
Add 3/4 cup of milk.
Repeat.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: meatball nibbles
directions: Mix ground beef, soup mix, cracker crumbs, eggs and milk together well.
Make into small meatballs.
Brown in skillet or bake in 400° oven for 5 minutes; set aside.
Melt jelly, ketchup and blackberry wine together and pour over meatballs.
Put in serving dish.
Keep warm when serving.

title: date ball candy
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook eggs, sugar and dates over low flame until syrupy.
Remove from heat;
add Rice Krispies and pecans; mix
well.	Butter	hands
well and roll mixture into bite-size balls, then roll in coconut.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and chocolate chips in double boiler slowly. (Do not allow to steam.)
Add at least 15 ounces of peanuts.
Drop onto wax paper and chill until solid.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with rolling pin.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Roll in small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: grilled chicken wings
directions: In medium bowl, stir all ingredients together except chicken. Place chicken in a glass dish; pour sauce over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator about 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut in colander for 15 minutes.
Cut in 1-inch pieces. Place in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Store covered in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: aunt lynn's brownies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together, then mix in the rest of the ingredients in descending order. Place in a greased and floured 9 x 12 pan. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Check to see when middle is clean with toothpick.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven as directions state on the cake mix box.
Use a 13 x 9-inch glass pan (this is very important!).
Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple together.
Place into greased glass pan. Crumble cake mix on top of this mixture.
Top with coconut, pats of butter and walnuts.
Cook as directions on cake mix box state.

title: caramel cake icing
directions: Mix ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan and place on medium heat, stirring occasionally until it comes to a rolling boil.
Let it boil for 1 minute on rolling boil, then remove from stove and let stand about 10 minutes.
Beat until smooth and begins to thicken.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water.
(Batter is very runny, don't worry!)
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Mix well and chill 2 hours prior to serving in a ball with crackers.

title: spanish steak
directions: In slow cooker, brown meat in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add everything; cook until meat is tender.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: Let boil 1 minute and beat;
add vanilla.

title: special k loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a
9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Pour filling into unbaked crust and bake at 350° until done.
Yields 8 servings.

title: better than robert redford cake
directions: Mix and spread flour, nuts and margarine into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese with sugar; fold in 1/2 of whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Add milk to pudding mix and beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Spread pudding mixture over cream cheese, then remaining whipped topping over pudding and garnish with nuts.
Let stand at least 2 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: diet veal scallopini
directions: Sprinkle veal with flour, salt and pepper.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, heat butter and oil.
When butter melts, add veal and cook for 3 minutes on each side.
Remove to serving platter and keep warm.
Add mushrooms, chicken broth and wine to skillet.
Cook until mushrooms are tender and liquid is reduced to a thickened sauce.
Pour over veal.
Sprinkle with parsley. Makes 4 diet servings.
Contains 255 calories per serving.

title: lazy fruit cobbler
directions: Juice can be substituted for water if canned fruit is used. Use 1/2 cup water with juice if using frozen peaches.
One cup Bisquick mix can be substituted for the flour and baking powder, if desired.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Roll potato strips in melted butter, then in the combined remaining ingredients.
Place on baking sheet and drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°, or until tender.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together in bowl. In saucepan combine cornstarch, sugar, water, rind and juice. Bring to a boil. Cook until thick. Pour over fruit while hot. Keeps in refrigerator for several days. Serves 10-12.

title: mint punch(lemonade)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand for 2 hours.
Boil sugar, lemon rinds, mint and water for 5 minutes. Cool.
Strain the mixtures into a punch bowl. Add the ginger ale and ice.
Mix and serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and put in 1 measuring cup.
Finish filling measuring cup with water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over jello, then add ice cream while hot.
After it dissolves, pour in pineapple and nuts.
Pour in flat dish.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: aloha chili
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in olive oil until tender. Add ground chuck and sausage; cook until done and drain off oil. Add chili powder and garlic powder; mix well.
Add beef broth.

title: macaroni and tuna casserole
directions: Place cooked macaroni and tuna in a bowl and add mustard, salad dressing, lettuce and pepper.
Mix well.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Chop.
Mix dressing and chill dressing and vegetables 2 hours before mixing all together.

title: can't stop corn pops
directions: Boil for 7 minutes butter, sugar and water.
Add vanilla. Pour over Corn Pops.
Mix together.

title: all-american lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in large pan.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano and garlic powder.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours over medium heat.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Alternate layers of noodles, sauce and cheese in greased 4-quart casserole or 13 x 9-inch cake dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until cheese bubbles on top.
This freezes well.

title: salsa
directions: *For mild (4 to 6), medium (7 to 9) or hot (10 to 14).

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each one.
Dissolve soda into sour milk and add to creamed mixture.
Place flour in a large bowl and add dates, orange slices and nuts to the flour; stir until all are well coated with flour.
Add coconut.
Add all of this to the creamed mixture, mix by hand as it makes a very stiff dough.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250°.
Cut into squares before completely cold.

title: sweet potato-peanut butter casserole
directions: Peel potatoes, cut into thick slices and boil until tender. Reserve 1 cup of the liquid.
Combine the liquid with the next 4 ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat in peanut butter.
Line baking dish with potatoes and pour mixture over.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.
This recipe came from the Georgia Department of Agriculture in the 1950's.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Stir together cornstarch, ginger, broth and soy sauce until smooth; set aside.
In large skillet, in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry half of the chicken strips until browned.
Remove and set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix fruits and nuts. Combine with cooled liquid jello. Congeal 1/2 mixture in 12 x 8 dish. Spread sour cream over congealed jello mixture. Top with remaining 1/2 jello mixture and refrigerate until firm.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix well the shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Mix flour and salt.
Stir in. Divide dough in half. Blend red food coloring into one half.
Roll 1 teaspoon each color dough on lightly floured board into a strip about 4-inches long. Place strips side by side.
Press lightly together and twist like a rope.
Put on ungreased baking sheet. Curve top down for handle of cane.
Bake 9 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove while still warm.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Sift together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Beat in eggs and oil.
Stir in grated carrots, flavoring and nuts.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool 45 minutes before removing from pan.

title: baked fudge dessert
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Pour into an ungreased baking dish.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Cut muffins in half.
Cream butter and cheese.
Add next four ingredients.
Drain crabmeat and squeeze dry.
Add to mixture. Spread in muffin halves.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cajun soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven or soup pot over high heat, cook sausage, onions and bell peppers.
Add tomato juice, tomatoes, remaining vegetables and ingredients.
Stir frequently.
Cover and reduce heat to medium-low, then low, allowing to cook for an hour or longer.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Saute onion, celery, pepper, garlic and Italian seasoning in oil; set aside.
In bowl combine beef, sauce, bread crumbs, egg white, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Add sauteed mixture; mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Another 8 ounce can of tomato sauce can be sweetened and poured on top before baking.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening by hand.
Beat in 1 egg at a time with a mixer.
Add flour and milk, then vanilla and lemon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open door until time is up.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: caribbean potato salad
directions: In a small covered saucepan cook potato, covered in 2-inches boiling water, until just tender, about 10 minutes. Drain and cool.

title: eloise's ohio buckeyes(candy)
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and confectioners sugar and form into balls.
You can start mixing with mixer and then use hand as it thickens.
Form ball the size of buckeyes.
Freeze on cookie sheet until firm.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add 3 tablespoons paraffin.
Use a toothpick to hold the ball and lower 2/3 of it into the chocolate (to look like buckeye).
Cool on a cookie sheet.
May be frozen.

title: prize coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly in bowl.
Stir in milk.

title: red hot applesauce
directions: Melt red hots in 1/2 cup water over low heat.
Add jello, 1/2 cup water and applesauce.
Let stand overnight.
Tastes great on toast!

title: dessert cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool cake.
Then mix vanilla pudding and spread over cooled cake after it thickens.
Drain pineapple.
Spread over pudding.
Spread topping over pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crust with rolls.
Chop vegetables into small pieces and put on top (broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, carrots and mushrooms).
Makes good appetizer.

title: jane's coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Add milk and egg yolks, stirring until smooth.
Cook over boiling water 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add 1 cup coconut.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar.
Put on top of pie. Sprinkle with coconut.
Brown in 350° oven.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: Cook onions in margarine until clear.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Season to taste. Serve warm with corn chips.

title: fresh corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and place in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix egg and oil together.
Add cake mix and mix with fork until all cake mix is moistened.
Form into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: jezebel, jezebel
directions: Mix preserves, jelly, horseradish and mustard.
Pour over the block of cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.
This mixture keeps well in the refrigerator for months.

title: mama's pancakes
directions: Blend butter, egg and milk.
Stir together sugar and flour. Mix wet mix into flour.
Stir and cook.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve 1/3 cup water and gelatine.
Add 2 cups water, 1 1/2 cups sugar and red food coloring.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Mix 1/3 cup water, cornstarch and pinch of salt.
Add to boiling mixture. Boil until clear.
Add 1 cup more sugar.
(If berries are sweet, I only add 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar.) Let cool; spread some on pie shell.
Slice layer of bananas over shell.
Fill with strawberries and mixture.
Chill overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter sides of saucepan.
Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and butter.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves and mixture is boiling.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, to 275°.
Add nuts and continue cooking to 295°, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in soda. Immediately pour onto buttered baking sheets.
Spread as thin as possible.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: buttermilk pecan chicken
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Dip chicken in the egg mixture and then coat with flour mixture.
Place in a baking dish making certain butter is on both sides.
Sprinkle with coarse pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the buttermilk, whipped topping and pudding mix.
Stir in the oranges and pineapple.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, add the cookie crumbs.
Serves 4.

title: corn chowder
directions: Dice bacon and fry in a saucepan until golden brown.
Remove from grease with slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towel.
Pour off all fat except 1 tablespoon.
Chop the onion fine and saute in bacon fat until limp.
Reduce heat and add corn and enough milk to make desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve in soup bowls with bacon pieces sprinkled on top.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil mac curls and cool.
Mix ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, stir in and top with a little Parmesan cheese.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, oil, eggs and sour cream in mixer bowl; mix well.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl; mix well.
Pour half the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle half the cinnamon mixture over batter.
Add remaining batter; sprinkle with remaining cinnamon mixture. Swirl back and forth with knife.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cut up 1 cup berries.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan.
Stir until smooth.
Add the cup of berries.
Cook and stir until thick and clear.
Add a few drops of red coloring. Cool.
Stir in remaining berries, saving 1/4 cup.
Pour into pie shell and chill 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip and remaining berries.

title: pigging outs
directions: Combine baking mix, sausage and cheese in bowl; mix well. Shape into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 10.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Put cubed bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle fried bacon, ham and grated cheese on top of the bread cubes.
Put bacon grease on top.

title: chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. In separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder and soda. Stir in oatmeal, corn flakes, chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Combine dry ingredients with wet ingredients; mix well. Drop batter 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly.
Use a "40 ice cream scoop."
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Center of cookies should be soft when taken from oven.
I get 85 cookies.

title: egg custard
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 10 minutes at 400°.
Then turn oven to 350° and cook until 1/3 of center still shakes.
Remove from oven; it will finish cooking as it cools.

title: apple pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend.
Add nuts or raisins; blend. Bake in a
9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lime molded salad
directions: Let set in fridge.
When it starts to mold, add grapes or crushed pineapple.
Let it chill, then combine 2 cups miniature marshmallows and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Put on top and sprinkle nuts and coconut over the top.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, salt, raisins and water.
Heat in Dutch oven or kettle.
When hot, add biscuits, cut in quarters. Cover and steam for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: thinner fritter batter
directions: Put egg
yolks and milk into bowl.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add to milk mixture.
Beat on medium until blended, scraping bowl
often. Beat in butter and lemon juice.
Add egg whites;
beat
only until blended. Frying temperature at 375°. Time:
3 minutes for onion rings.

title: spinach hors d'oeuvre
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all cheeses (grate sharp cheese).
Cook and thoroughly drain chopped spinach; set aside.
Add onions to cheese mixture.
Use liquid margarine to grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take a damp towel and place on counter.
Add a piece of wax paper on top, then place filo dough on top (about 26 sheets).
Take each piece of filo dough and place on a piece of wax paper or foil and brush on (all over) each piece and start layering, using 1/2 the box of filo dough or approximately 13 pieces.

title: frozen fruit squares
directions: The night before serving, combine marshmallows with sour cream and refrigerate overnight.
Marshmallows will partially melt in sour cream.
The next day, combine banana, fruit cocktail and coconut.
Toss lightly together; do not crush.
Fold in marshmallow mixture.
Turn into 2 freezing trays and chill at least 1 hour.
Do not freeze solid.
Cut into squares or scoop into sherbet glasses.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Crush crackers and saute in butter. Mix together remaining ingredients and put into 2-quart casserole. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly (uncovered).

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease two 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer pans.
Spray bottom and sides with pan coating (i.e. Pam).
Sift together dry ingredients into large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended.
Pour into prepared pans.

title: beauty jello salad
directions: Stir raspberry and black cherry Jell-O with the boiling water until dissolved.
Stir in the can of pie filling.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix together sour cream and marshmallows and spread on top of firm Jell-O.
Refrigerate again.

title: cheese dreams
directions: Cut muffins into halves.
Spread cut slices with soft margarine.
Cut bacon into halves.
Set oven control at broil or 550°.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and garlic.
Drain.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well and simmer for 10 minutes.
Layer half of meat, tortillas, sour cream and cheese in 9 x 13-inch dish. Repeat layers.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: frozen potatoes casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together.
Put hash browns in casserole dish.
Cover with onions and cream mixture.
Top with cheese and put crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight or all day.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients except pecans in medium bowl with wire whisk or hand beater until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake in preheated 375° oven 40 to 50 minutes or until center is set. Serves 8.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir and microwave for 2 more minutes.
Use with your favorite chips.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt together 2/3 cup butter and 1 1/2 cups brown sugar firmly packed.
Add above ingredients.
Beat well and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: chicken and coke(french smothered chicken)
directions: Place chicken in deep skillet or casserole dish. Pour salt, ketchup and Coke mixture over chicken. Cook in 300 degree oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: date toffee cake
directions: Cook the dates, water, sugar and lemon juice to a thick paste. Cool.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Place half of oatmeal crumbs in a 9 x 12-inch pan, top with date mixture.
Put balance of oatmeal crumbs on top.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt oleo.
Add condensed milk, nuts, powdered sugar and coconut; mix well and roll into bars.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
When hard, put toothpick in each ball and dip in hot chocolate mix.
Set on wax paper until dry.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake
in
x 9 x 2-inch pan at 250° for 1 hour. Serve with following icing.

title: c-b-c casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain.
Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine; mix soup, milk and Cheez Whiz together.
Heat.
Put vegetables in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour hot soup mixture over all. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients (except paprika, seasoning salt, garlic salt, Accent and hot sauce) in a large pot over medium heat. Add the paprika, salt, Accent and hot sauce according to your own taste. Reduce heat and simmer over low flame for about 1 hour. Makes approximately 1/2 gallon of sauce.

title: chunky fruit oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in skim milk, egg white and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in dried fruit and nuts.
Drop with teaspoon onto prepared cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart.
Bake 13 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer half an hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and brown sugar.
Add soda-water mixture.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add eggs, oatmeal, vanilla and raisins.
Place on cookie sheets by teaspoons.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Put margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Cool about 45 minutes before eating.

title: neal's white chocolate macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter. Add eggs.
Beat well into creamed butter.
Add vanilla.
Add sugars and beat well.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Crumble nuts on bottom of pan. Place cake and pudding mixes in large bowl.
Add rum, water, oil and egg.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt Jell-O in hot water.
Add whole cranberry sauce to Jell-O until dissolved, then add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: soft oatmeal cookie
directions: Blend together shortening and eggs.
Add liquid from raisins with the soda added.
Beat in flour, cinnamon, salt and oatmeal.
Add the boiled raisins.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Add butter, cream cheese and 1/3 cup milk or cream.
Whip with mixer on low speed or mash with potato masher, adding remaining milk or cream as needed to make potatoes light and fluffy.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons water.
Add eggs, sugar, milk and 1/2 of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add rest of the flour and butter; beat.
Store overnight in refrigerator.
Take out next day and knead on floured board.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise before baking.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Rinse broccoli; cut broccoli flowers at the ends of the stems. Coarsely chop
flowerets.	Place in bowl and add salad oil, salt, pepper and	lemon
juice.
Mix
well
and
chill 30 minutes.
Mix tomatoes and broccoli.
Blend the sour cream and mustard together. Toss
with
broccoli
and	tomatoes, mixing well.	Serve on lettuce
cups.
Refrigerate 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: gladys beach's sauce for stir-fry
directions: After liquids boil, pour in flour and water mixture.
Cook until all is mixed together.
Serve with stir-fry vegetables.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in a large skillet.
Stir flour into the meat; mix well.
Immediately add the milk; stir continuously until thick.
Add more milk if too thick.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican dip
directions: Melt together in microwave or double boiler.
Stir well.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: deviled egg casserole
directions: Halve eggs; remove yolks and mash with 3 tablespoons sour cream, salt and mustard.
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Melt butter and saute peppers, onions and mushrooms until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in pimento, soup and remaining sour cream. Place 1/2 of sour cream mixture in a 1 1/2-quart shallow pan. Arrange eggs, cut sides up, in the mixture.
Pour remaining soup mixture over eggs and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until blended.
May be prepared in advance and reheated.

title: mushroom royale
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove mushroom stems and finely chop them (approximately 1/4 cup).
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and cook stems, green pepper and onion until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients except whole mushrooms.
Fill mushrooms with stuffing and dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake 15 minutes, letting boil for 2 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Break corned beef up into small pieces over kraut.
Spread grated cheese on as next layer.
Mix 1000 Island and mayonnaise and spread on top of cheese.
Top with bread crumbs or croutons.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and casserole is warm.

title: cabbage gumbo
directions: Melt shortening and cook onion and peppers slowly over low heat for a few minutes.
Add the chopped cabbage, tomatoes, okra, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Last put enough water to cover and cook 30 minutes.

title: pecan torte
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: hot nutty chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, almonds, onion, celery, lemon juice, salt and mayonnaise.
Put in a flat baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 mins. or until bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut stalks from broccoli; peel and chop.
Chop onions and combine with broccoli; add bacon that has been crumbled into small pieces, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Toss these ingredients together and cover with dressing made of mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Refrigerate until serving.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pumpkin pecan harvest bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together pumpkin, egg whites and oil.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add brown sugar and mix well. Add the flour mixture to the pumpkin mixture in 2 or 3 stages and combine well.
Beat with a whisk or electric mixer at medium speed for about 2 minutes.
Stir in chopped pecans.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Cream together eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix flour mixture a little at a time with the sugar mixture.
Mix together well.
Add apples and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Let cool before slicing.

title: italian spinach dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and stuff turkey or chicken lightly. Spoon out from cooked turkey in tablespoon size ovals on a platter for serving.

title: squash
directions: Cook squash and onion until done; drain.
Add beaten eggs, milk, sugar, margarine, salt and pepper.
Layer squash and cheese; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray nonstick cooking spray (Pam, etc.) on baking dish or pan. Spread 1 1/2 cups of rice in pan.
Slice mushrooms and place on rice.
Place chicken breasts on top, skin side up.
Pour 1 cup of wine over chicken.
Mix 1 can of mushroom soup and 1 can of water and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on chicken.
Cover tightly with tin foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
No peeking as escaped steam leaves rice uncooked!

title: mound cake
directions: Bake and split layers.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix, undrained Mandarin oranges, eggs and vegetable oil in a bowl and pour into the 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Pour pineapple in large boiler (pot) and heat.
Add dry jello, then cool.
When cool, add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour into container (at least 9 x 9-inch).
Refrigerate. Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: salty treats
directions: Melt chocolate; add remaining ingredients to chocolate.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: aunt bessie's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.

title: beef stew
directions: Dissolve tapioca in V-8.
Combine all ingredients; cook in a 250° oven for 5 hours.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cool and crumble cornbread. Drain pinto beans. Mix all ingredients. Chill in refrigerator 2 hours. Serve cold.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel
and
slice
potatoes
to	approximately
1/4-inch thick. Rub
margarine
around
the inside of the bowl.
Layer all ingredients,
starting
with
potatoes and ending with the cheese. Layer
potatoes,
onions, ham, cheese, etc.
Pour the soup over the top and cook in a slow oven until done (approximately 325° for 1 hour).
tags: cream of potato soup or cream of celery

title: arlene's no mess lasagna
directions: Spray deep 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer sauce, noodles, meat, onion, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat.
You may not use all of your noodles.
Add 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Bake at 375°, covered with foil, for 1 hour, then, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: italian garden saute
directions: Saute vegetables, except tomatoes, until tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Add tomatoes.
Heat and serve immediately.

title: pasta salad(for a crowd)
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Cut up veggies as indicated; mix together in a bowl.
Save some of the marinade from the artichoke hearts and the mushrooms.
After rinsing and draining pasta, add veggies and cheese.
Mix well, then add the dressing and a couple of ounces of the marinade.
Mix well, then cover and chill.
Makes a very large salad; serves up to 20 as a side dish.

title: beef and gravy on rice
directions: Mix beef and soups.
Pour into a baking dish and bake until beef is tender, about two hours at 350°.
Pour over a bed of prepared Minute rice.

title: california cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Crumble Blue cheese.
Chop olives.
Mix cheeses, stir or mix in olives.
Shape into one large ball or 2 to 3 smaller ones.
Roll in chopped walnuts.
(Some nuts may be mixed in with the cheeses, if desired.) Wrap in plastic.
Store in refrigerator.

title: coleslaw with tomatoes
directions: Rinse cabbage, remove dark tough outer leaves.
Cut cabbage in 1/2 and then into quarters.
Remove core.
Shred cabbage finely with knife or food processor.
Core a green pepper.
Remove seeds and ribs.
Cut pepper into thin rings.
Slice onion and separate into thin rings.
Cut cherry tomatoes in half.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: easy beef roast
directions: In a slow cooker, put your roast.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup as directed.
Pour over roast and cook on medium setting overnight.

title: grandma miihlbach's punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, pineapple and sugar to taste together.
Then add sherbet.
Always add 7-Up last.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Cook grits in water (add salt and parsley) until thick. Cool slightly.
Grease tube pan.
Turn grits into pan spreading	up sides
and	center	with back of spoon.
With greased hand, press evenly to completely line the pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar and salt together.
Combine eggs and milk.
Mix with corn mixture.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir from the bottom 2 to 3 times during the first 30 minutes of baking time.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on the bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on package. Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls over cake mix before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back.
Leave to cool.
When cooled, you will understand its name!

title: surprise dessert
directions: Mix together thoroughly and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: deluxe potato salad
directions: Add salad dressing to potatoes, celery, onion, pickle juice, pimento and eggs.
Toss lightly until well blended.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or more before serving.
Garnish with additional hard-cooked eggs.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake your cake.
While your cake is cooking, clean strawberries.
I use a lot of strawberries.
It depends on you. In another bowl, take part of your berries and mash them.
Add some powdered sugar, depending on how sweet you want them.
When cake is done, let cool.
If you make a square or oblong cake, cut layer in half.
Add mashed berries on bottom half and a layer of Cool Whip.
Put top back on.
Add Cool Whip all over the cake, then decorate with strawberries.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water; bring to a boil, then simmer 1/2 hour.
Remove chicken breasts and allow to cool for a few minutes, then cut into bite size pieces.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients to pot.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat; cook for 1/2 hour.
Add more water if needed.

title: kathy's mushroom bread
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients until mushrooms are barely done. Section bread in 1-inch diagonals, keeping bread in a whole. Spoon little of mushroom mix between each slice. Also, insert pie shape of cheese in each slice.
Wrap loaf in foil and bake at 300° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix all together; salt and pepper to taste and top with this mixture:
2 cups Ritz crackers, mixed with 1 stick oleo (melted).

title: chocolate peanut butter brickle
directions: Place crackers on foil-lined cookie sheet, butting them up to each other. Melt margarine; add sugar and boil 2 minutes. Pour over crackers and bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with chocolate and peanut butter morsels. As they melt, spread evenly over baked crackers.
May sprinkle with nuts or coconut. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Break.

title: chicken with milk and rice
directions: Wash the chicken pieces.
Place them with the water in a saucepan and boil; add the cardamon seed, mastica and salt.
Cook for 1 hour.
Remove chicken pieces and set aside.
Strain broth and place in the saucepan with the rice; allow to boil, then simmer.
Add the cream to the milk; mix well.
When the rice is cooked, add the milk mixture, gently stirring.
Heat the butter and stir in the 2 pieces of mastica.
When melted, pour immediately over the rice and cover for 5 minutes.
Stir the rice mixture and serve in a platter with the chicken pieces on top.

title: grandma's easy gourmet stew
directions: Don't brown meat.
Don't add water.
Put stew beef into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread cream of mushroom soup evenly on top. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 3 hours in a 350° oven.
Serve with wide noodles and fresh carrots.
The kids will love it!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well and pour in graham cracker crust.

title: pureed carrot and ginger soup(good hot or cold)
directions: Saute onion, ginger root and garlic in cooking oil in soup pot over low heat until soft.
Add stock, wine and carrots and simmer until carrots are very tender, about 40 minutes.
Cool. Puree solids in food processor until very smooth.
Return to pot and add cooking liquid until desired consistency is reached. Season with curry powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot or cold with chopped parsley garnish.

title: garlic cheese creamed potatoes
directions: Fix potatoes same as mashed potatoes.
Add other ingredients. Top with cheese.
Put in oven and melt cheese.

title: succotash
directions: In large skillet, brown bacon lightly.
Spoon off all but 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet; add onion and green pepper. Cook 5 minutes.
Add lima beans, corn, tomatoes, salt, sugar, pepper and butter and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
In cup, blend flour with 2 tablespoons water; stir into mixture and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: easy pumpkin swirl
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Line top and sides with wax paper.
Grease wax paper.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into pan and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: whirl and drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Lightly grease a baking sheet. Combine all ingredients in the bowl of the food processor, fitted with steel blade.
Process until well mixed.
This will not form a stiff dough.
Remove bowl from processor.
Remove blade and then using a large spoon, drop biscuit-size dollops of the dough onto baking sheet, spacing about 2 inches apart.
Bake for about 12 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are lightly browned.
If desired, brush tops with butter after removing from oven.
These biscuits are crispy on the outside and feather light on the inside.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Mix water and flour, alternating.
In the last amount of flour, add soda and baking powder and a pinch of salt.
Chocolate should be mixed in last. Mix well and add a capful of vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan or about 25 to 35 minutes for layer cake.

title: bev's peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage on candy thermometer the sugar and milk.
While warm add Marshmallow Fluff, vanilla and peanut butter. Then add chopped nuts, if desired.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: prisnjac
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Cut into squares.
Serve as a breakfast dish (can freeze).

title: banana bread
directions: Blend sugar, margarine and egg yolks. Add water alternately with the flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in the mashed bananas. Then, fold in the egg whites. Place in greased and floured bread tins. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. If small bread tins are used, cut baking time to 45 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler(or top of the barn cobbler)
directions: Melt
butter
in large casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and milk. Pour over batter.
Put fruit in center of batter but do not stir. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Batter will rise up over fruit.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread rye bread with mustard.
Between layers, put sauerkraut, Swiss cheese and corned beef (either canned or thin sliced).
Butter one side of sandwich, then place on a hot grill or skillet.
Butter other side before turning to brown other side.

title: chocolate whiskey layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans (2 round).
Mix cake mix, buttermilk, oil, eggs and whiskey.
Beat at low speed 2 minutes.
Increase to medium for 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost.
Press pecans on sides, if desired.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Cook in crock-pot on high 10 to 12 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chili for a crowd
directions: Season beef with salt and brown in 10-quart kettle.
Add onions and green peppers; cook until tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients except the kidney beans.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add water if needed for desired consistency or add more sauce.
One-half hour before this is done, add kidney beans.
Serve hot with bread and a salad.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolates and sugar with water.
Add evaporated milk and bring to a boil over medium heat, cooking about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla, continuing to stir until smooth.
Serve over ice cream balls that have been rolled in toasted pecans.
Sauce can be reheated in microwave.
Add a little milk to desired consistency.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil. Cover and cook 1 minute. Cool slightly, then add last 2 ingredients.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix Cool Whip, yogurt, berries and orange peel until blended. Spoon into serving bowl.
Refrigerate.
Serve as dip with strawberries, grapes, kiwi, oranges or pineapple.

title: lemon sauce and variations
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually add boiling water, bringing to boil.
Cook over low heat until thickened and clear. About 15 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and rind. Add nutmeg and butter. Serve hot over pudding and other desserts. Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onions, green pepper and garlic for approximately 3 minutes, then add remaining ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add fettucini and toss and heat through. This recipe serves 4.

title: rice pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except rice.
Put rice in last. Give it 1 stir.
Pour in greased square glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon before serving.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in double boiler.
Add other ingredients except vanilla.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in already baked pie shells. Top with meringue.
Makes 2 pies.

title: oliff's stained glass cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in double boiler.
Put marshmallows, nuts and melted chocolate in large bowl and mix well.
Put 4 sheets waxed paper (24-inches long) down and put flaked coconut on paper.
Put mixture on wax paper and form log roll shape.
Freeze overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: peach sauce
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1 1/4 cups syrup. Coarsely chop peaches. In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; add reserved syrup. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; remove from heat. Stir in orange peel, orange juice, butter or margarine and chopped peaches. Cover and chill without stirring. Serve over ice cream, pound cake, waffles or filled crepes. Makes 3 cups sauce, 16 servings.

title: fontina, corn and jalapeno quesadillas
directions: Heat 2 teaspoons oil over medium heat.
Add corn, chilies and oregano and saute 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Heat clean skillet over medium heat.
Brush with oil.
Add 1 tortilla.
Cover with 1/2 cup cheese and 1/4 of corn mixture.
Top with another tortilla.
Cook until tortillas are brown and cheese melts, about 2 minutes per side.
Cut into 8 wedges.

title: crock-pot pinto beans
directions: Wash pinto beans.
Place in crock-pot and cook on high for 45 minutes.
Drain water from beans and rinse them again.
Place back in crock-pot with water to cover them.
Add bacon pieces.
Cook on low for 6 hours or until done.

title: french toast
directions: Melt and mix together brown sugar, butter and corn syrup. Pour into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Peel, core and slice apples; put over top of mixture in pan.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Cut bread 1 inch thick.
Place bread on apples, then pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 40 minutes.

title: pound cake wafers
directions: Mix in order and drop by little balls on a slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caramel cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, dry ingredients and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crostini
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Slice baguette into 16 very thin diagonal slices. For ease in slicing, freeze loaf for about 30 minutes. Slice each tomato vertically into 4 (1/4-inch) slices.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Mix in glass jar or cruet.
Let stand several hours before using.
Keeps for a long time in refrigerator.
Good on green salads.

title: watermelon surprise
directions: Wash and dry melons.
With long sharp knife mark off a 5 to 6 inch circle and cut a deep cone into each melon.
Remove the plug. Turn melons over and drain for 30 minutes.
Discard the juice. Turn melon right side up and pour 1/2 to 1 c. liquid margarita mix to fill cavity, wait a bit and add more at it is absorbed.
(If using dry Margarita mix, prepare as directed and then fill melons.)

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Makes approximately 5 servings.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Cook blackberries for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 stick butter while cooking.
Put in 9 x 12 baking dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour over blackberries.
Bake for 30-35 minutes at 350 degrees or until brown on top.

title: vegetarian delight
directions: Wash and shred bok choy and cabbage with sharp knife.
Peel, wash and shred carrots on a grater.
Cut up green and brown onions and add with black pepper, all-purpose seasoning and salt to shredded vegetables.
Cover and leave to season for 20 minutes. Then heat oil in saucepan until very hot.
Throw vegetables into heated oil in saucepan and stir until cooked.
Do not cover while cooking.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Serve with white rice.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine oleo and sugar; roll into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Cover balls with chocolate mixture.
Let harden on wax paper.
Makes a large amount.

title: rolled banana finger goodies
directions: Cut bananas into 1 to 1 1/2-inch bite-size pieces.
Roll bananas in Eagle milk, then roll again in the nut and coconut mixture.
Be sure all pieces are covered completely.
Chill in refrigerator.
Makes a great refreshing finger food for parties.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and milk until sugar is dissolved.
Add chocolate syrup, whipping cream, vanilla and salt.
Blend well. Pour into freezer.
Add milk to fill line.

title: artichoke shrimp
directions: Put oil (about 2 tablespoons) in pot you will use to cook in. Put chopped onions and shrimp in pot and stir around until shrimp are pink.
Add all the rest of ingredients except cornstarch. Bring mixture to boil and cook about 15 minutes.
Add dissolved cornstarch to thicken.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Can substitute boneless cubed chicken or cubed beef for shrimp.
Cook longer.

title: meat loaf and gravy
directions: Mix ground beef, 1 teaspoon onion mix, bread, egg and milk. Cook 1 hour; drain off grease.
Mix 2 cups water, onion soup and brown gravy mix.
Pour over meat loaf.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil fryer until tender.
Cool broth.
Remove bones and cut chicken in small pieces.
Chop onion and pepper; saute in margarine until tender.
Heat mushroom soup diluted with 1 can of water.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Cook and drain lasagna noodles.
Divide smoked sausage into 6 pieces.
Split lengthwise and stuff with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap each piece in a noodle.
Place in a baking dish and cover with sauce.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: sangria
directions: Combine wine and orange and lime juices with sugar in a large pitcher; stir until sugar is dissolved. Add Cointreau and chill. Just before serving, add club soda, ice cubes and orange and lime slices.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water/wine and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning.

title: old black witch's magic pancakes
directions: Take a bunch of water, not too much.
Pinch gently to feel if it is soft.
Place over a hot fire.
Don't forget to use a pan. Close your eyes until water sings.
(Watched pot never boils.)
If not successful first time, it is probably too hard.

title: toffee candy
directions: Cook butter, sugar, corn syrup and water to a hard boil (300°).
Spread into
greased
pan.
Melt
6 chocolate bars on top.
Sprinkle
with
finely chopped pecans.
After the chocolate hardens, turn
candy
over onto wax paper.	Melt 6 chocolate bars and
spread
on candy.
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans. Break into bite-size pieces.

title: personal pizzas
directions: Split open the English muffins and put them on a cookie sheet. Mix tomato sauce with spices in a small bowl.
Grate the Mozzarella cheese.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons sauce on each muffin half.
Top with pepperoni and grated Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tomato noodle soup
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan, combine water, tomatoes and carrots. Cover, bring to a boil, approximately 5 - 10 minutes.
Add beef base and noodles; stir.
Lower heat simmer for 15 minutes or until noodles are cooked.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread into a large bowl.
Add chopped pepper, onions, tomatoes, pickles, bacon, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix together well.
In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, pickle juice and sugar until creamy.
