Pour over salad and stir well until dressing has coated salad.
Chill.

title: tater beef casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread beef.
Sprinkle onion soup over beef.
Mix cream soup with milk; pour over meat.
Layer Tater Tots over top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: cherry delight
directions: Put cherries in oblong greased pan.
Pour dry cake mix over cherries; then pour melted butter over that.
Put nuts on top. Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut meat in strips and cover with sauce; soak overnight.
Hang strips in oven rack to dry out.
Set oven at 200°.
Let dry for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cherry dream pie
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar; put 1/2 the mixture in bottom of a square baking dish (save other 1/2 for the top).
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
If mixture is too thick, add a little milk, then layer cream cheese mixture and cherry pie filling.
Add remaining graham cracker crumbs to the top.
Chill overnight.

title: cool vanilla salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk.
Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Break cookies into chunks.
Stir in cookies and pecans.
Top with cherries.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix honey, vinegar, lemon juice and grated onion together. Add other ingredients to honey mixture.
Slowly add oil while beating with mixer.
Yields 1 pint.

title: strawberry party punch
directions: Combine cranberry strawberry drink, ice milk and strawberries in a large punch bowl. Use a rotary beater or wire whisk to thoroughly combine ingredients until creamy. Gently stir in soda just before serving. Makes about fifty 1/3-cup servings.

title: zeytinyagli yaprak sarmasi(stuffed grape leaves)
directions: The filling can also be used for stuffing green peppers, eggplants, cabbages and tomatoes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Grate and mix together the Longhorn cheese and gherkin pickles.
Chop up and mix in the pimientos and onion.
Mix in mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Refrigerate a few hours and serve with crackers.

title: mango salad
directions: *(Or 2 cups boiling water, 2 cups cold water and 1/4 cup cold water and 1 package Knox gelatine.)

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla and crushed pineapple, then a portion of flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add water alternately with the remaining flour and stir only until smooth.
Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff, and place in 2 (8-inch) greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and ice between layers and on top and sides with seven-minute icing.

title: crescent roll squares
directions: Spread dinner rolls flat in baking pan. Add condensed milk. Pour over rolls. Add coconut pecan frosting over milk.
Melt the butter and pour over the frosting.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. When cool, cut in squares.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flavors and buttermilk. Sift together flour, soda and salt; add.
Mix well.
Add German chocolate that has been softened in warm oven or in double boiler. Blend together well.
Cook in 9-inch stem pan that has been well-greased and dusted with flour, about 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Test with toothpick.
If done, toothpick will come out clean when inserted in cake's center.
Place cake under a tight fitting cake cover while still hot and leave covered until cold.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drench bacon rolls.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Baste occasionally.

title: beef-noodle casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and garlic.
Cook noodles in boiling water; drain and add meat.
Add soups and mushrooms.
Put in greased casserole.
If grated cheese is used, put over top.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: baked pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pasta as directed on the bag in a large bowl.
Combine pasta, spaghetti sauce and 2 cups of cheese. Mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Uncover.
Then top with remaining 2 cups cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 10 minutes longer, uncovered, or until cheese melts.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: cranberry orange relish jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Pour 3/4 cup jello in mold and chill.
Chill remaining jello until thickened.
Place oranges in jello mold to form a pattern.
Blend nuts and relish and add to thickened jello.
Spoon on top of jello in the mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold onto plate and garnish with sprigs of mint leaves.

title: coconut pralines
directions: Mix sugar, soda and salt in a large skillet. Add milk, stirring well to mix with dry ingredients. Cook approximately 15 minutes over medium-high heat until mixture reaches the soft ball stage (approximately 235°). Stir constantly and scrape the sides of the skillet as you stir. Once the mixture reaches the soft ball stage, add the coconut and continue to boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and beat by hand 2 to 3 minutes until it thickens. Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper or buttered surface. Let cool. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken, onion, soup and broth together. Pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish. Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, pepper, margarine and milk. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake 1 hour (or until crust is brown) at 350°.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Put jello and puddings in saucepan.
Add 2 cups hot water and bring to a boil.
Simmer until thick and bubbly.
Cool completely. Fold in mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on lettuce or on rye bread.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Put potatoes in enough cold water to cover them in a stockpot. Cover, bring to a boil and cook at a moderate boil until tender. Puree the potatoes with their liquid; set aside.
Saute the onion in butter and oil over medium heat. Add chopped carrot and celery and cook approximately 2 minutes. Add vegies to pureed potatoes in the stockpot.
Turn heat to medium and add the Parmesan cheese, milk and broth. Stir and cook for a few minutes until consistency reaches liquid cream. Salt and parsley to taste.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan generously with Crisco.
Let bread defrost only long enough to slice.
Slice each loaf into 11 to 12 slices. Dip each slice into melted oleo and let stand up as best you can in Bundt pan.
Set aside and let rise to top of pan.
Bake on next to bottom shelf of oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In center of each tortilla, place 1/4 cup chicken, 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 tablespoon salsa.
Roll up. Arrange, seam side down, in 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with remaining salsa and cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: gourmet crab ring
directions: Sprinkle
gelatin
over water to soften.
Stir over hot water until
dissolved.
Beat with cream cheese until smooth. Stir
in the next 5 ingredients and 2 tablespoons of parsley. Pour
into 3-cup
ring mold.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until
set.
To serve,
turn
out on a plate and garnish with remaining parsley. I place green pepper strips around.

title: garlic cheese biscuits(like served at red lobster)
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese together for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Mix margarine and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from sheet. Makes 12.

title: king cole salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Add dressing. Blend well. Cover and chill.

title: oven fried potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Scoop out the inside, leaving a thin layer of potato.
Place skin side up on a pan and let dry, 1 hour.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Roll out each biscuit flat.
Spread a small amount of mustard on each biscuit.
Put a piece of cheese on each one, then roll a Vienna up in biscuit.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake according to biscuit directions.

title: crab casserole
directions: Saute green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter.
Crumble crackers and add all to crab meat.
Crumble remaining crackers and place on top of casserole along with remaining butter.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
You can also add more or less of the ingredients according to your taste.

title: chef salad
directions: Divide lettuce among 4 large plates. Top each with 2 oz. turkey, 1 oz. cheese, 2 tomato wedges, 1/2 carrot and 1 oz. of dressing.

title: apple coleslaw
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; toss well and set aside.
Combine next 7 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Pour over cabbage mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill 8 hours. Serve with a slotted spoon.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla in large mixing bowl. Beat well. Add milk to egg mixture gradually. Beat until smooth. Pour custard into baking dish. Sprinkle custard with nutmeg. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape into balls; flatten slightly and crisscross with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.

title: orange juice fizz
directions: Y'all were looking for "No Ho-Hum Breakfasts."
Here's one I found in Fast and Healthy Magazine.

title: three vegetable primavera
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; drain.
Return to cooking pot, cover to keep hot.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; press into 10-inch spring-form pan. Sprinkle 1 quart of blueberries over mixture.
Combine and pour the remaining ingredients over blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabrillo casserole
directions: Saute beef and onion; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning mix and water.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Pour 1/4 cup bottled taco sauce into each of three 9 x 13-inch casserole dishes.
Turn and coat 5 tortillas per casserole in sauce.
Cook spinach, drain and press out all water.
Stir one-half of spinach into beef mixture; divide spinach-beef mixture in half and spoon evenly into the 3 casseroles.
Sprinkle half of cheese evenly over each casserole. Cover each casserole with 5 tortillas and 1/4 cup bottled taco sauce.
Add remaining spinach and beef mixture.
Spread each casserole with one cup sour cream.
Scatter remaining spinach over each casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes in 375° oven.
Uncover and bake 25 minutes longer. Makes 30 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute meat until slightly brown; add chopped onions and minced garlic.
Allow to cook with meat until the onion is soft.
Add chili powder and salt.
Mix well, then add mashed tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cover and let simmer while preparing Part 2.

title: wheatmeal shortbread
directions: Begin by beating the butter in a bowl and gradually working in the flour, ground rice, sugar and salt (using your hands at the end to form the mixture into a stiff dough), but don't work it too much or the butter will get oily.
Then divide the dough in half, and roll out one piece to a 6-inch round.
Now transfer the round to a greased baking sheet, pinching all around the edge to decorate. Then, using the back of a knife, mark the round into 8 wedges and prick all over with a fork.

Do the same with the remaining piece of dough, then sprinkle both rounds with a little caster sugar. Now bake just below the center of the oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until both shortbreads are tinged brown and feel firm in the center.
Then remove them from the oven, sprinkle again with a little more caster sugar and leave until cooled a little before cutting each round into the marked wedges.
Cool them on a wire rack and store in an airtight tin.
If you prefer, you can roll the dough out to a 1/2-inch thick round and cut the shortbread into wedges with a small fluted cutter.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving 1/2 cup pecans.
Chill slightly. Shape into ball on plate.
Cover outside of ball with chopped pecans.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar in a bowl.
Mix bourbon and syrup; stir into cocoa.
Mix well.
Add crumbs and nuts; mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Drop in a bowl of powdered sugar; coat well.
Let dry for several hours.
Freeze well.

title: all-bran rolls
directions: Combine boiling water and shortening and stir until melted. Add sugar, bran and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Combine with first mixture.
Add beaten eggs. Add flour a little at a time, mixing well.
If using the same day, let rise or put in refrigerator (covered).
Leave until ready to use.
Shape into rolls and let double in size.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham slices. Place dill pickles on cheese. Roll ham up. Cut in 1 1/2-inch sections.

title: creamy potato soup(serves 6)
directions: In 5-quart saucepan, in oleo, cook potatoes and onion until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Add water, salt, pepper and bouillon.
Reduce heat to low and simmer about 15 or 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk.
Makes 4 1/2 cups, 185 calories per serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into pieces and put in baking dish.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat eggs and add with milk.
Mix up and put 1 cup raisins into mixture.
Mix again and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
I set baking dish in another pan of water and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: apple-raisin-nut salad
directions: Dice apples.
Put in remaining ingredients.
Stir to coat. The kids will love it!!

title: peck's brown rice
directions: Stir and place all in a covered casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until tender and the liquid is absorbed.

title: burgers in-a-hurry
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Knead for a few minutes.
Shape into six patties.
Fry in lightly oiled skillet or bake on oiled cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve on whole wheat bread or buns.
Top with lettuce, tomato, alfalfa sprouts, grated carrot, onion, pickles, catsup or mustard.

title: michael and jen's favorite coffeecake
directions: Take 2 cans refrigerator biscuits and cut them in fourths with a scissor.
In brown lunch bag, put 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Shake a few cut biscuits at a time in the bag.
Place them in a Bundt pan.
Bring one stick butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon to a boil.
Pour over the top of the shaken biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Nuts can be put in the Bundt pan, but they don't like them.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Combine in a large bowl the fruit cocktail, cottage cheese, Jell-O, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix all together.
Add pecans on top.
Cover and place in refrigerator before serving.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes and cheese.
Stir in potatoes.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or 3-quart casserole bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
(Eight cups of cubed potatoes can be substituted for the frozen potatoes, if desired.)

title: crispy potato pancake
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of oil and butter in skillet.
Add shredded potato.
With fork, press potato into an even layer that covers bottom of pan.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook over medium-low heat until bottom is well browned.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Slide pancake onto a large lid or plate.
Put remaining oil and butter in pan and invert cake back into pan. Press in again with a fork and cook until well browned.
Slide onto plate and sprinkle with green onion.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: In
a heavy frying pan mix sugar, dates and well beaten eggs. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture pulls away from sides of pan, about 5 minutes.
Cool this mixture about 3 minutes, then add vanilla and nuts.
Carefully add corn flakes and Rice Krispies cereal.
Wet hands in cold water and form mixture into balls about the size of walnuts.
Roll each ball in coconut and cool.
Easy, different and delicious.

title: baked pork n' beans
directions: You can make leftover mashed potatoes into croquettes.
Put the cold mashed potatoes into a bowl and add one or two egg yolks. If you don't eat eggs, use grated cheese instead.
Add salt and form into little balls.
Roll in bread crumbs and bake on oiled sheet until light brown in a 375° oven.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread.
Then add bell peppers, onion, tomatoes, seasoning
and salad cubes.Then add 1/2 of the bacon bits.
Add mayonnaise then the remaining bacon bits on top.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Add boiling water and mix well. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.
This cake freezes well.

title: creamy carrot casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots until crisp-tender, drain, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid. Place carrots in a 3 quart lightly greased baking dish. Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish and liquid, spread over carrots. Sprinkle with cheese. Toss bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle over cheese. Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°. Yield 16-20 servings.

title: marinated fruit
directions: Drain fruit well and conserve juices.
To juices add Tang and vanilla pudding.
Mix well and pour over fruit, keeping bananas on bottom until mixed for serving.

title: lemon bars(goofy bars)
directions: Mix cake mix and melted margarine.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In mixer, mix powdered sugar, eggs and cream cheese. Beat well and pour over crust in pan.
Put nuts on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 300° or until mixture is light brown in color.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes.
(If use about a teaspoon of dough per
cookie.)
When
removed	from
oven, loosen each cookie, then allow to
cool on pan about 5 minutes.
Remove to paper towel and
cool
completely
before
storing in airtight container.

title: sandwich fill
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This makes 1 large loaf of bread, (14) sandwiches. (If cut into party size one inch sandwich (quartered), this will make 56 sandwiches per loaf).
Very good.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Place one layer of cake squares in serving dish.
Spread one can of Chocolate Pudding over Cake squares.
Then sprinkle crushed Heath Bars over the pudding, remember to leave enough Heath Bar mix to cover remaining layers of cake squares and pudding.

title: sesame bread for bread machines
directions: Measure flour in large mixing bowl.
Add baking powder and salt and mix well.
Work in shortening until distributed evenly. Add lukewarm water.
Mix well, working dough until smooth.
Cover. Let stand for 20 minutes.
Roll out on floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in 3 to 4-inch squares.
Fry in deep hot oil until golden brown on both sides, turning once.
This recipe can be halved for a family of four.

title: pizza dough
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, yeast, salt and sugar.
In saucepan, heat milk, water and oil until hot to touch (125° to 130°).
Stir hot liquids into dry mix.
Mix to desired consistency.
Knead until smooth (add additional flour if needed).
Rub with oil.
Let rise until double in size.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and sour cream together.
Mix sugar and poppy seed together.
Pour into cake batter, stirring well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam and sprinkle with sugar and repeat this.
Pour batter into pan, spreading evenly.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined eggs, milk and margarine, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries. Spoon into greased and floured medium-size muffin pan.
Fill each cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: quick peanut butter snacks
directions: Mix ingredients and form into small balls.
No cooking or refrigeration necessary. Ready to eat.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half and spoon out yolks. Mash up yolks and add relish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Fill the inside of the egg whites with mixture and top with sliced olives. Makes 12.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain all beans.
Brown meat and onions; drain fat.
In a large, 13 x 9-inch, oblong dish, combine beans, meat and rest of ingredients.
Cover and bake in slow oven at 325° for 2 hours. Great for group or picnic.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Put vegetables in a casserole dish.
Combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 of the can of French fried onions.
Pour this over the vegetables.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 more minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Salt and pepper boned chicken breasts.
Wrap each in a slice of bacon. Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° until almost done.
Mix 1/2 cup sour cream and 1 can mushroom soup.
Place each breast on a piece of dried beef in a shallow baking dish. Pour soup mixture over and bake for 30 minutes or longer.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; can also use Italian Free dressing.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let come to a boil.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise and soup and add to chicken mixture.
Layer rice in casserole dish. Top with chicken mixture.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Mix together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in flour mixture.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry goodness
directions: Dissolve in hot water Jell-O.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into mold and refrigerate until semi-solid.
Remove and spread sour cream evenly over entire mixture.
Pour remaining Jell-O mixture over this and refrigerate.

title: corn pancakes
directions: Mix all together; fry on both sides on hot oil.

title: mochiko chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Add
chicken; marinate
for 2 hours or longer (overnight	for
more
taste). Fry in oil until brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir 1 package Knorr vegetable mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until well blended.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Next put the green onions in and stir well again.
Chill 2 hours.
Stir again before serving.
Serve with crackers, veggies or mountain bread.
Pumpernickel bread is also great cut or pulled off into small chunks to dip in mixture!
Enjoy, it's delicious!

title: sauce for ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place cooked ribs, bone side down, and brush with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn ribs over; brush with sauce and broil about 10 minutes.
This sauce works well on chicken.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper in skillet; drain. Put in bottom of casserole dish and spoon soups evenly over top of meat, then add a layer of Tater Tots on top of meat and soups. Bake in 350° oven until Tater Tots are brown.

title: beef fillets with debra's sauce
directions: Rub fillets with garlic powder and ground pepper.
Wrap with bacon (optional).
Put kosher salt in iron skillet on high heat. When very hot, sear steaks 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Remove steaks, reduce heat to medium-high and deglaze skillet with wine. Add beef stock; use wooden spoon to get all goodies from bottom of skillet.
Crush garlic cloves, green peppercorns and black peppercorns in a cloth, with a hammer or use pepper mill if it's too hot in garage to get hammer.
Add mixture to sauce.
Add cognac; reduce heat until sauce is semi-thick.
Add whipping cream (1/3 or 1/2 pint or more, depending on your current weight). Return steaks to skillet for 1 more minute.
This is a straight shot.
Serve with something to sop in sauce.

title: e j b.b.q. chicken
directions: Beat eggs, add oil and beat again.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Add chicken pieces and marinate in refrigerator over night.
Makes 6 chicken halves.

title: rose's strawberry pie
directions: When ready to make pie, carefully lift ripe, red berries into a bowl of lukewarm water.
Then lift them into a bowl of cold water. Finally stem and use immediately.

title: pecan carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Sift other dry ingredients into oil and sugar mixture.
Blend, then add alternately with beaten eggs.
Add carrots and pecans.
Bake in 3 layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttercream icing recipe
directions: Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Be sure to store in covered container.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and set aside to cool.
Eggs may be sliced and placed on top as garnish or mixed in with other ingredients.
Mix ingredients and put in oblong baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch) or large mold.
Pour Jell-O over all.
If dish or mold is lightly oiled, salad will come out more easily.

title: cheese sausage mold
directions: Melt cheeses.
Saute sausage until done; drain thoroughly. Mix cheeses and sausage; add peppers.
Mold in well-greased or oiled Bundt or angel food cake pan which has been lined with plastic wrap.
Chill 6 to 8 hours.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter.
Pour over popcorn and mix, then shape into balls.

title: pumpkin raisin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Into mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Make a well in center.
Add pumpkin mixture.
Blend just until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in pecans and raisins.
Turn batter into loaf pans.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil in bowl until light and fluffy, add eggs 1
at a time, beating after each addition.	Mix bananas. Dissolve soda
in
buttermilk.
Add to creamed mixture alternately
with sifted
flour
and salt, beating well after each addition.	Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until bread is brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix 3 cups mashed sweet potatoes, 1 stick margarine, 1 cup sugar, 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir well.
Then pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: honey thyme vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into hot vegetables.
Add salt to taste.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and combine with buttermilk.
Add this to dry ingredients.
Stir well and then knead.
Add more flour, if necessary.
Roll out on floured board, about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush tops with melted butter and margarine; bake until golden brown.
Cut biscuits may be frozen on cookie sheets until hard and then placed in plastic bags and kept in freezer until needed.

title: black cherry and sour cream jello
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Let cool.
Add sour cream; mix with hand mixer, then add drained cherries and nuts.

title: cheese and pea salad
directions: Drain peas; combine cheese with mayonnaise and celery.
Toss together lightly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Chill cooked, cleaned shrimp thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients except lettuce and mix with shrimp.
Serve in small sherbet glasses or cups lined with heart leaves of lettuce.
Makes 5 servings.

title: fall apple dip
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Slice apples and dip in orange juice before serving.
Also good with ginger snaps.

title: imperial chicken bake
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Dip each chicken breast in milk; dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine butter, garlic and lemon juice; drizzle over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay out crescent rolls on a cookie sheet and bake.
Mix dressing ingredients.
Spread on crust when cooled.
Cut up veggies and put over crust.
Add cheeses.
Put under broiler until the cheese is melted.

title: lentil stew
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in large kettle; bring to boil. Saute onion, mushrooms and basil in oil.
Add to other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
This stew tastes like it has meat in it.

title: peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Boil milk, sugar and butter for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Slowly stir in oatmeal. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: salsa and cheese dip
directions: Spread softened Neufchatel cheese in bottom of 10 inch pie plate.
Layer rest in order.
Microwave until hot and bubbly. Turn plate a few times while cooking.
Serve with tortilla chips. Enjoy!

title: creole burgers
directions: Brown ground meat and chopped onions in skillet, stirring to separate meat particles.
Stir in soup, ketchup and mustard.
Add pepper; simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon on buns.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Cut excess fat from meat and cut into uniform pieces if necessary.
Place in a casserole and add the two cans of soup.
Do not add seasoning.
Cover; bake at 300° for 3 hours.
May add a little water, if necessary.
Serve over cooked and drained wide noodles or rice.

title: flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
This custard recipe requires a baking dish that will fit in a baking pan thus allowing "double boiler" cooking.

title: creamed onions
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add sour cream and chives.
Stir in potatoes, one at a time while hot, adding milk if necessary to achieve creamy texture.
Add garlic powder and salt.
Put in baking dish.
Brush top with melted butter, then sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate or freeze for later.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Thaw before baking.

title: chip dip
directions: Use your crock-pot for making and serving dip.
Place both ingredients in crock-pot until melted and blended.
Serve right from the crock-pot (on warm) with tortilla chips.

title: sausage and pepperoni pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Crumble sausage into medium skillet. Cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally. Remove sausage and drain on paper towels. In a large, lightly greased casserole dish, layer 1/2 of cooked noodles, 1/2 of sausage and 1/2 of remaining ingredients. Repeat with second layer of noodles and sausage. Layer remaining cheese and pepperoni, reserving several pieces of pepperoni slices to garnish top. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: potato fudge
directions: Stir confectioners sugar into mashed potato until stiff.
Add package of coconut and mix in.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch square pan. Top with your favorite type of chocolate, melted.
(Example: chocolate chips, Hershey bars, etc.)

title: one dish meal
directions: Put all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Good!!

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper; drain.
Mix everything together.
Cook on low heat 10 minutes.
Serve over corn chips.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a casserole dish.
Top with dressing mix crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cake
directions: Oil pan.
Place chopped pecans on bottom of pan.
Place 1 layer of coconut on top of pecans.
Mix Duncan Hines cake mix as the directions state.
Pour on the layer of pecans and coconut.
Then mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake until cake is done.
Do not overbake.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook and drain lasagna noodles.
In a bowl, combine cottage cheese, Mozzarella, Parmesan cheese, parsley, eggs and vegetables. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread spaghetti sauce on bottom.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans, combine all ingredients and toss lightly. Cover, refrigerate overnight.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Shake and chill olive oil, sugar, white vinegar and soy sauce. Shred cabbage, like lettuce.
In large bowl, toss cabbage, onions, almonds and sunflower meats.
Just before serving, crunch up Ramen noodles and put in bowl with cabbage.
Toss with dressing.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix well. Add milk, then coconut.
Pour into pie shell and cook at 350° until done.

title: mock salmon molded salad
directions: Let
the cream cheese come to room temperature, so you can cream it with mayonnaise.
In a pretty good sized bowl, sprinkle the gelatine over the cold water and let it stand while you heat (but don't boil) the tomato soup.
Add heated soup to gelatine and let cool.
When cool, add the cream cheese and mayonnaise.

title: jalapeno chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Add soups, sour cream, onion and peppers.
Mix.
Cut tortillas into quarters.
Layer tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese twice. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes two 8 x 8-inch casseroles.
May be frozen.
(I cook this in the microwave on medium for 10 minutes.)

title: puffs
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture; start and end with milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in small muffin tin.
Melt 1/2 cup butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over puffs.
One recipe makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Add all together and simmer for 3 hours.
Take meat out of pot and shred the meat.
Put the meat back into the pot.
It's done.

title: english country wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in glass jar.
Makes 16 cups.
Add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to each cup of hot water.

title: toasted pecan balls
directions: Roll round scoop of ice cream in chopped nuts until well coated.
Place in dessert dish. Add toppings. Freeze the nut coated ice cream balls until ready to serve.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain and wash pickles.
Cut in quarters or chunks.
Bring sugar, vinegar and seed to boil.
Let cool. Pour over pickles. Store in glass jar in refrigerator.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Slice peppers and onions.
In large skillet, brown meat in butter; add garlic and broth; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and peppers.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Blend cornstarch, water, and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture and cook, stirring until clear and thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Put meat in bottom of casserole. Cover with soup; add wine. Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°. Stir once. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spicy rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage, cumin and garlic powder, stirring often.
Drain.
Add onions and green peppers; saute until crisp-tender.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Simmer until the chicken is tender and the sauce thickens.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, oats, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Arrange 1/2 the apple slices in buttered 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 the sugar mixture over apples.
Top with remaining apples and sugar mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: cream of carrot and rice soup
directions: Slice carrots and onion.

Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat. Add carrots and onion. Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in stock, rice, salt and pepper (white pepper if you have it). Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, 30 to 40 minutes. Run through blender; return to saucepan. Add cream.
If too thick, add water or stock.
Place over low heat and bring to a simmer.
Garnish with parsley or chives.

title: sweet rib sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and boil gently for 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins(makes 18)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Set aside. Combine next 3 ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Stir in apples.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cream and 1 package of pudding. Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy taco hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease. Add tomato juice and spaghetti sauce mix; simmer.

title: the what-ever cookie
directions: You can use any kind of cake mix, chocolate, lemon, white, spice or what-ever kind of cake mix you would like.
You can also mix in chocolate chips, nuts, butterscotch chips or anything that would be good in cookies.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl. Place in casserole dish sprayed with PAM. Bake 1/2 hour at 350 degrees. Then crush 1 tube of Ritz crackers and melt 1 stick of butter, mix well and place on top of casserole. Continue baking until brown on top.

title: "doctored up" pickles
directions: Heat and mix sugar, vinegar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over pickles in a large container.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before use.
May be packed back into jars and refrigerated.
Yields 8 pints.

title: white christmas fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Mix 3 cups flour with salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Mix 1 cup flour with fruits and nuts.
Add to mixture and stir well.
Grease tube pan. Place 2 or 3 layers waxed paper on bottom and sides.
Pour batter into pan.
Pour 2 cups water in shallow pan.
Place on bottom shelf of oven underneath cake.
Bake in preheated oven at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tests done.

title: fudge
directions: Preheat oven to high and turn it off.
Melt butter in a shallow pan in oven.
Add pecans and sprinkle lightly with salt. Set in oven and stir occasionally until toasted.
Butter should not brown.
Combine sugar and evaporated milk in top of double boiler. Put over boiling water and stir to dissolve sugar.
Let boil for five minutes.
Remove from heat and add both types of chocolate and the marshmallow cream.
Beat until chocolate is melted and smoothly blended, then stir in nuts.
When mixture begins to thicken, pour into two buttered 8 or 9-inch square pans.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 4 pounds.
It can be halved.

title: rigatoni
directions: Brown sausage; add Ragu and seasoning.
Cook noodles and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sausage and Ragu mixture.
Next, layer pepperoni on top and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.
(Also freezes well.)

title: cold linguine salad
directions: To cooked linguine, add cut up tomatoes and sliced cucumbers. Add cut up olives and mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients well with Salad Supreme and dressing.
Make right before or several hours ahead of time so salad will marinate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese, sausage and Bisquick together until mixture sticks together.
If necessary, add 3 to 5 tablespoons water.
Form into small balls the size of a walnut.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: finnish oven pancakes
directions: Heat milk in microwave.
Mix flour, salt, eggs, milk and oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mix in pan.
Sprinkle sugar on top. Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 45 minutes.
Lower oven if too hot.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and garlic until hamburger is brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer.
Stir occasionally.
Cook for at least 1 hour.
Cook longer, and it's even better (at least 4 hours). Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: unbelievable pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; mix 2 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread.
Set aside to cool.
Add chopped peppers, onion and eggs.
When bread is cooled, crumble into a large bowl. Fold in the crumbled bacon.
Then gently fold in chopped tomatoes and mayo.
Refrigerate.
Better if made the day before.

title: polynesian meatballs
directions: Meat Balls:
Combine all ingredients and form into small meat balls.
Fry in small amount of oil, browning on all sides.
Remove from oil and drain.
These may also be browned in oven on a baking sheet.

title: sunday morning raisin loaf
directions: Heat the oven to 325°.
Lightly butter a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Heat the orange juice until it is almost boiling.
Put the raisins, butter and orange rind in a bowl and pour the orange juice over them.
Set aside to cool in another bowl.
Beat the eggs with the sugar.
Add the vanilla; stir into the raisin mixture in another bowl.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to the raisin mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Fold in the walnuts.
Lightly spoon the batter into the loaf pan.

title: delightful peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients except bell peppers and cheese.
Clean and hollow out bell peppers and stuff with mixture.
Top with cheese. Place in covered baking dish and bake at 375° for 50 minutes. Remove cover and bake another 10 minutes.

title: quick red velvet cake
directions: Mix the cake following the package directions and then add the buttermilk, cocoa, eggs and food coloring, mixing well.
Bake according to instructions on the cake mix box.
Ice as desired.

title: chalupas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, cheese, chilies, olives and green onions together.
Save 2 cups aside.
Add diced chicken.
Spoon chicken mixture into flour tortillas and roll up.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan seam side down.
Spread reserved sauce over the top. Sprinkle with additional sliced olives, sliced green onions and grated Cheddar cheese to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hot cheezy crab dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in double boiler until well blended and hot.
Serve in chafing dish with toast points or Melba toast.

title: lo-cal pineapple chicken
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Lay in chicken breasts. Add onion soup; cover with dressing and pineapple juice.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Add pineapple; bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: meringue
directions: In small pan, mix cornstarch and cold water until blended. Stir in boiling water and cook over medium heat until comes to a boil.
Stir until thick (about 2 minutes).
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add juice to egg whites and beat until stiff. Gradually add sugar, beating well until whites stand in peaks. Add cornstarch mixture all at once and beat until well blended.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions, pepper, celery and garlic. Cook until they are wilted.
Add tomatoes which have been cut in small pieces.
Sprinkle on 2 tablespoons chili powder plus large can of chili.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Scald 1 1/2 cups milk in the top of a double boiler.

Make a thickening by combining the sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt, then stir in the remaining 1/2 cup milk with the egg yolks. Stir this flour mixture into the hot milk and cook until it thickens. Remove it from the heat and add the butter and vanilla.
Let it cool a little before pouring into a baked pie shell.

title: corn casserole
directions: Spray Pam on pan.
Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours; it should be lightly browned.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Add sour cream to juice mixture.
Let all this cool and then add pineapple and cubed pear.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown beef in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine. Transfer meat to plate.
In same skillet, add remaining 1 tablespoon butter and cook mushrooms and onion until tender. Return meat to skillet; add water and steak sauce.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles (4 servings).

title: waikiki chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat chicken with flour.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken and brown on all sides.
When browned remove to shallow roasting pan, arranging pieces, skin side up. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, vanilla, water and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour with soda and salt.
Blend into shortening mixture.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake.

title: peachy ham slice
directions: Gently saute ham in butter.
In a saucepan, combine water, sugar, jelly, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Peel, half and pit peaches and place cut side down in sauce.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Turn and cook 5 more minutes.
To serve, place ham on platter and garnish with peaches and sauce.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl with fork. Pour into loaf pan and bake 55 to 65 minutes.

title: tiffany's favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and mix with other ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.
(Just don't tell Tiffany it had mayonnaise in it.)

title: cornflake macaroons
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Stir in cream of tartar and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff and glossy.
Fold in nuts, coconut and cornflakes.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoons onto well greased baking sheets. Bake in 325° oven for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: edie's chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and cocoa and blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 small unbaked pie shells. Place on bottom rack of oven preheated to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: four bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (beans, etc.).
Mix sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over the bean mixture.
Let set in refrigerator for at least overnight to marinate.

title: sherried roast pork
directions: Shake flour in oven bag.
Place in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put meat in bag.
Combine soy sauce, sherry, garlic, mustard, ginger and thyme.
Pour over meat and close bag with twister.
Marinate overnight, turning frequently.
Make 6 slits in oven bag and insert meat thermometer through bag into roast (optional).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat reaches 170°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream butter and oil.
Add brown sugar and cream well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift together flours, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened. Gently fold in strawberries and pecans.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients except cornflakes and 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes, mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in bottom of punch bowl.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Layer over cake.
Layer remaining ingredients in following order:
bananas, pineapple, strawberries and whipped topping.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: german chocolate upside-down surprise cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put nuts and coconut over bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar in a bowl with mixer until thin.
Pour this over the cake (be careful not to let this touch the sides of the pan).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crusty potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and shred; you need 8 cups.
Add enough water to cover potatoes, preventing discoloration, until all are shredded. Drain potatoes, saving 1 cup of the water.

Heat water, 2 tablespoons butter (or margarine) and milk to just under boiling. Pour over potatoes and stir in the onion, salt, pepper and eggs. Melt the remaining 2 tablespoons butter and spread into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour potato mixture into pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven until set in center and edges are browned and crusty, about 50 minutes. Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: potato candy
directions: Add vanilla to	mashed	potato.
Gradually
work
sugar into potato until the right
consistency
to
roll out (as for pie crust).
Spread with
peanut butter.
Sprinkle with pecans and cherries if desired.
Roll	up (as for jelly roll).
Chill and slice.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat slightly in shortening. Add other ingredients in order listed. Add about 2 quarts water. Bring to simmer and simmer slowly, stirring often until done. May have to add a little water along.
It is better after it sets a few hours. Can be frozen.

title: cheese and marshmallow salad
directions: Mix pineapple and grated coarsely Velveeta cheese with the mayonnaise.
Add marshmallows and fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add Ro-Tel, soup, and broth. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
In a large casserole dish, layer chips, chicken, sauce and cheese.
Top with a few crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until cheese is melted and casserole is heated through.
Can be heated in microwave for 15 to 20 minutes.
I use Tostitos chips and Velveeta cheese. Use mild Mexican Velveeta to make it extra spicy.

title: chocolate pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift 1 1/2 cups flour, cinnamon and baking powder in large bowl.
Stir in 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until crumbly.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs and remaining ingredients except pecans with blender until blended. Pour over dough in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes.

title: five-cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: ditto bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix well.
Press into a buttered 10 x 15-inch pan.
Combine remaining 4 ingredients and melt until smooth.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Once frosting sets, cut into bars.
Store in an airtight container in a cool place.

title: instant spiced tea mix(also called russian tea mix)
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Spoon into jars and seal.
To serve, add 2 teaspoons of a cup of boiling water.

title: doesn't taste like cranberries cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine dry cake mix, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl. Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until crumbly. Stir in nuts; set aside. Combine peach filling and cranberry sauce in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan; mix well. Sprinkle crumb mixture over fruit. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato sauce, onion and seasonings (mixture will be thick).
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat into biscuits.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Makes 12 pizza cups.

title: out of this world rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Let stand 10 minutes. Combine dissolved yeast, eggs, 2 1/2 cups flour, 1 cup warm water, shortening, sugar and salt in a large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl, for 2 minutes. With a wooden spoon, stir in remaining flour to make soft dough. Cover.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Punch down; refrigerate overnight. Three hours before baking, roll out as desired.
Cut 1 inch thick and dip in butter.
Let rise covered, for 3 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown hamburger meat with garlic, onion and bell pepper, chopped.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Add chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, tomato soup, water, Ro-Tel and drained corn. Cook noodles; drain.
Layer in casserole dish the noodles, meat mixture, most of cheese and noodles.
Save rest of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour; right before casserole is done, add rest of cheese to top and melt.

title: hamburger noodle stroganoff
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Drain excess fat.

title: strawberry angel food freezes
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together.
Add Cool Whip, frozen strawberries and nuts.
Mix well.
Cut round angel food cake into 4 layers.
Frost between each layer.
Add the rest to top and sides of cake.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Let cool and pour over chicken pieces.
Refrigerate until ready to cook.
Cook chicken on skewers with any vegetables you want (green pepper, red pepper, onions, mushrooms, pineapple chunks).

title: chiles rellenos
directions: *An easy way to crush tortilla chips is to remove most of the chips from a full bag and crush the remaining chips in the bag with your hands.

title: shredded wheat dessert
directions: Dip each biscuit into milk to soften and split it open.
Fill with sugared chopped nuts.
Melt butter and place in baking pan. Bake in warm oven 350° for about 20 minutes until slightly browned.
Pour syrup over them after removing from oven.
Serve warm or cold.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Measure all ingredients into a large bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping side and bottom of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: simply peachy cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, blend all cake ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the beef and bacon.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.
Drain excess fat.
Blend flour and seasonings into meat mixture.
Stir in soup and cook slowly, uncovered, stirring frequently 20 to 35 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through. Serve over noodles.

title: mushroom pork chops
directions: Place cooking oil in skillet and heat.
Add pork chops, cook at medium heat turning until done.
Remove pork chops from pan. Pour in soup and heat until lumps are gone.
Place pork chops back in pan and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Great with rice or potatoes.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in cake pan for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corny bread bites
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full with batter.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Mini muffins are great.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Melt shortening, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine shortening and yeast mixture with beaten egg and stir in flour.
Knead.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and refrigerate for 2 hours. Divide dough in half.
Roll out into 12-inch circles.
Cut each into 8 pieces.
Form crescents by rolling from the rim to point. Place on cookie sheets and let rise.
Bake at 450° until well browned.

title: apricot punch
directions: Heat jello, sugar and water.
Mix with other ingredients except 7-Up.
Freeze.
Add 7-Up before serving.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix and heat.
Stir until smooth.
Good with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: corn cabbage
directions: Heat pressure cooker and brown bacon.
Place browned bacon on a plate.
Add cabbage, corn and pepper to bacon drippings.
Season with salt and brown sugar.
Add water.
Place cover on cooker. Allow steam to flow from vent pipe to release all air from cooker. Place indicator weight on vent pipe and cook 3 to 5 minutes with stem at cook position.
Cool cooker at once.
Garnish with bacon strips and paprika.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in preheated 325° oven.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Put cracker crumbs on bottom of greased baking dish.
Mix all ingredients well but not until mushy.
May be thinned with 1/8 to 1/4 cup of milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with more cracker crumbs. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat with salt, pepper and onion. Assemble in deep casserole dish. Cover bottom of dish with a layer of meat, then add a layer of potatoes., then a layer of cheese; repeat. Cover and bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, chicken soup, sour cream, cheese, 1/2 cup melted margarine, salt and
onion;
put
in
x
9-inch baking dish.
Top with cornflakes
mixed
with
1/2 cup melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken packets
directions: Cook chicken with onion in 1 tablespoon oil.
Drain off excess fat.
Mix in bowl cooked chicken, sour cream, cream cheese and milk.
On greased cookie sheet, unroll 2 packages crescent rolls and press each into a triangle.
Place chicken mixture on first triangle crescent roll; place other triangle over chicken mixture and pinch edges together to seal mixture in.
When pan is full usually fits four units.
Place in oven for 20 minutes at 350°. Makes approximately 6 to 8.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in double boiler.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Drain chiles and tomatoes.
Brown onions and chiles together; add tomatoes.
Mix all with hamburger and cheese.
Serve warm.

title: meal in one
directions: Bake a large potato and cut it open; flake the inside with a fork.
Add ham or chicken, green onions, tomatoes, bacon bits and top with cheese.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Bring butter and syrup to a boil.
Mix in confectioners sugar until it thickens (or add more confectioners sugar if necessary). Wrap 1/2 teaspoon of mixture around cherry with stem.
Cool in refrigerator 2 hours.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip wrapped cherries in chocolate mixture.
Then cool on cookie sheet.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: Peel, seed and coarsely chop apples.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, salt, water and shortening.
Add yeast mixture, raisins and apples.
Gradually add flour to form soft dough.
Turn out onto well floured surface and knead for 10 minutes, adding flour as needed to keep dough from sticking.
Dough should be smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double.
Punch down and form 2 loaves.
Place in 2 loaf pans (9 x 5-inch).
Let rise until higher than pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool out of pans.
After 10 minutes, butter tops of loaves.
Cool, slice and enjoy.

title: meaty nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown meats. Melt cheese in microwave. Mix together. Add soup and diced Ro-Tel tomatoes. Heat and serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli sole roll-up
directions: Place broccoli flowerets in microwave dish with 1/4 cup water and cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on High 6 minutes.
Grease four custard cups with margarine.
Arrange 2 sole fillets per cup so they are covering the inside edge.
Place microwave broccoli flowerets in center; flower heads up.
Cover flowerets with Swiss cheese.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Remove from cups carefully and serve immediately.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring in large bowl of electric mixer.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients and mix thoroughly with butter and egg mixture.
Work into batter with heavy spoon or hands the nuts and fruit.
Line angel food cake pan with foil. Bake slow in oven set at 275° for 3 hours.
Half hour before cake is done, brush top with honey.
Decorate with fruit and nuts and press down firmly.
Return to oven and finish baking.
When completely cool, remove from pan and remove foil.
Wrap with a wine dampened cloth.
Store in airtight container at least several weeks.
This blends flavor and mellows cake.

title: chinese treasure chicken
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken, cut meat into 1-inch pieces.
Combine chicken pieces with egg white and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
In
a
bowl,
mix
remaining tablespoon cornstarch with the
soy
sauce,
vinegar,
sugar and 6 tablespoons of the lychee syrup.
Drain lychees and discard remaining syrup.
Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Add chicken and cook on high heat for 3 minutes.
Add
candy, ginger and soy sauce mixture and lychees. Cook,
stirring
constantly
until
sauce
thickens.
Stir
in kumquats and cherries.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put aside 1/4 of onion rings.
Combine rest of ingredients. Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with rest of onion rings. Bake at 350° uncovered for 20 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots.
Add the chicken broth. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add potato soup, cheese, parsley, sour cream and sherry.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: Wash the beans and put into a saucepan along with stock and 1 tablespoon oil.
Cover, boil and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Chop onion and saute in remaining oil until soft.
Chop celery and leaves.
Grate potato and carrot.
Add these to onion and cook over medium heat for several minutes.
Add veggies to beans in the last hour they are cooking.
Add oregano, savory, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Simmer until done.
Add lemon juice.
Delicious served over cooked brown rice.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate on stove.
In bowl, combine margarine and chocolate with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add flour.
Put in greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.

title: orange slice cake and glaze
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and then add flour with milk and beat.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: golden carrots (hawaii)
directions: Mix carrots and pineapple bits in buttered baking dish. Combine
pineapple	juice,	brown
sugar,
tapioca,
salt
and butter.
Pour over carrots and pineapple bits.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: finger jello
directions: Pour and cool in flat container for 20 minutes. Cut into cubes and eat with fingers.

title: creamed eggs
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Chop eggs.
Add chopped eggs to the mixture.
Serve with toast for breakfast.

title: strawberry spinach salad(12 to 16 servings)
directions: Toast almonds in 400° oven on cookie sheet.
Stir about 10 minutes until golden brown.
Wash spinach, pat dry, remove stems. Tear into bite-sized pieces.
Combine spinach, strawberries and almonds in large bowl.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving pour Poppy Seed Dressing over salad and toss gently.

title: nacho potato slices
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Trim ends and cut potatoes into 3/8-inch thick slices.
In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish, arrange potato slices, putting smaller slices in the center. Sprinkle with green onion and green pepper.
Cover with vented clear plastic wrap.
Cook at 100% power (High) for 7 to 10 minutes or until tender, giving the dish a half-turn once.
Drizzle sauce over slices.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 to 60 seconds more or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: missy's glorified chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken in 2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle with butter. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Bake for 20 minutes more.

title: granola cookie bars
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add eggs; beat in vanilla and water. Mix oats, flour and salt. Stir in chocolate chips, coconut and raisins. Bake at 350° for 22 to 27 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix water and spices in large pan.
Cover and boil 10 minutes. Add cider and sugar.
Simmer 10 minutes longer on low heat.
Stir often to mix well.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and bananas.
Add lemon juice, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Check at 50 minutes.
Divide into 3 bread pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O with the hot water; chill 15 minutes, then mix in the other ingredients.
Put in dish.
Chill overnight.
Serve.

title: crawfish or shrimp casserole
directions: In butter, saute onions, bell peppers, parsley flakes and onion tops until clear.
Add everything, except rice, crawfish or shrimp. Cook a while longer, mixing well (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Add crawfish or shrimp and cook for 5 to 15 minutes.
Add cooked rice and stir well.
Pour into a casserole dish, cover with bread crumbs and bake in oven at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small skillet, heat olive oil until hot.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in red clam sauce, Italian style bread crumbs and cheese.
Place in a 2-cup ovenproof casserole.
Cover and bake until cheese is melted, about 20 minutes.
Serve at once with raw vegetables, crackers or chips. Yields 2 cups.

title: salsa
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Chill; serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well. Shape dough in balls the size of walnuts and roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately place 1 Kiss in center of each cookie.

title: chicken creole
directions: In a heavy 12-inch skillet, melt 1 tablespoon of the margarine over moderate heat.
Add the onion, green pepper, celery and garlic and cook, uncovered, until the onion is soft, about 5 minutes. Transfer to small dish.
Raise the heat under the skillet to moderately high and add the remaining margarine.
While it melts, sprinkle the chicken breasts all over with the paprika and cayenne pepper.
Add the chicken to the skillet and cook about 5 minutes, turning occasionally.
Add half of the cooked vegetables to the skillet along with the tomatoes, rosemary, marjoram and bay leaf; reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until the chicken is tender.
Whisk in the flour/chicken broth mixture and cook, stirring constantly until the sauce has thickened, about 3 minutes.
Return the remaining vegetables to the skillet and heat for 3 minutes.
Discard the bay leaf.
Serve with fluffy boiled rice and steamed okra.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine dressing and butter; spread half on bottom of pan. Mix soup, onion, chicken and peas; add milk.
Pour on top of dressing layer.
Add rest of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: donna church's vegetarian chili
directions: Heat oil in a 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook, covered, until vegetables are tender, but not brown.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, drained and rinsed kidney beans, raisins, etc. (everything except beer and nuts).
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in beer and 3/4 cup cashew nuts.
Return to boiling.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes more or until consistency desired.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: bean cake(fake name:  spice cake)
directions: Put raisins in boiling water for about 20 minutes and drain. Remove pork from pork and beans, then mash beans with fork.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and beans for about 2 minutes.
Blend flour into all ingredients (very thick).
Fold in raisins.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice. Pour over cake while still warm.

title: letter pretzels
directions: Dissolve the dry yeast in the water.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Slowly add flour mix to the yeast mix until about 3 cups are added.
Then knead in the last cup of flour mix.
Knead about 3 minutes.
Divide the dough and shape into letters.

title: night before french toast
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut bread into 1-inch thick slices and arrange in 1 layer in pan.
In bowl, mix remaining ingredients (except butter) thoroughly.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours as needed.

title: ruth's chocolate sauce
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar, cocoa and margarine (cut in small pieces) in saucepan; bring to rolling boil over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool and serve over dessert of your choice.

title: creamy roquefort dressing
directions: Beat until smooth the vinegar and oil.
Add Roquefort cheese, cream cheese and salt.
Blend in mayonnaise.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press sugar cookie dough into pizza pan to make a crust.
Cook at 350° until brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip. Pour on top of cooled crust.
Slice and layer fruit over this.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well; add lemon extract and buttermilk.
Pour in one 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cocoa pound cake
directions: Mix the flour and cocoa; set aside. Beat the butter and sugar 10 to 12 minutes until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well after each addition. Mix in vanilla with last egg addition. Add the cocoa flour mixture and beat just until smooth. Turn into greased and floured 5 1/4 x 9 1/2 loaf tin. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. (If using glass, bake at 300° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 275° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.) Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove and finish cooling on wire rack.

title: blueberry pie
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir together cornstarch and sugar; gradually stir in milk (keeping smooth).
Over medium heat, stir constantly.
Cook until mixture shows it is boiling (it bubbles and sputters and mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon). Take off heat.
With a wire whisk, gently stir in the sour cream and vanilla until well blended.
Fold in the blueberries.
Pour in crust.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cranberry relish
directions: In a food processor, chop the first 3 ingredients.
Transfer mixture into a mixing bowl and add the sugar.
Cover the bowl and place in the refrigerator.
Let stand overnight.
Wonderful for the Thanksgiving and Christmas holidays.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Take off bones. Combine soup, chicken and vegetables (drained) in large casserole dish.
Prepare stuffing according to directions and put on top of chicken vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes. Serve.

title: fried kebabs
directions: Cut chicken livers into pieces the size of the veal cubes. Blanch the sweet breads for 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain and remove membrane.
Cut into cubes.

title: stove top shepherd's pie
directions: In 10-inch ovensafe skillet, cook meat, onion and chili powder over medium-high heat until meat is cooked through and onion is tender, stirring to break up meat.
Stir in half the soup, the water and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar and whole cranberry sauce.
Break up with fork.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Peel and remove seeds from orange; cut up in small pieces. Peel and chop apple.
Add sour cream to mixture; mix well.
Add apple, orange, nuts, pineapple and juice.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken breast ala palace
directions: Flour chicken and saute in 1 tablespoon butter and olive oil. Cut peeled tomato in halves and add to chicken.
Add herbs, spices and chicken broth.

title: supper in a skillet
directions: Brown beef
in
skillet. Add tomatoes, water, onion and seasoning.
Bring
to a boil. Spread uncooked noodles over top of meat mixture.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Serves 6.

title: wassail
directions: Tie cinnamon and cloves in bag.
Mix and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Simmer for 20 minutes and serve hot.

title: chow chow
directions: Cut, combine and cook all ingredients until thick, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Put in canning jars and boil lids and rings. Put lids on jars while hot.
Turn upside down to seal.

title: helen jannett's best frosting
directions: Boil first three ingredients until sugar dissolves. Add semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Pour while hot onto cake.

title: applesauce diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is absorbed, add applesauce, sweetener, oil and eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to other ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Put in greased and floured pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until cake is done.
If you use a Bundt pan it takes 45 to 55 minutes.

title: coconut macaroon cupcakes
directions: In a large bowl beat egg whites with salt until they hold soft peaks.

Beat in gradually 1/2 cup sugar and continue to beat the meringue until it hold stiff peaks and is smooth and shiny. In another bowl toss together coconut, 1/4 cup sugar, almonds, flour and lemon rind.
Fold the mixture into the meringue.

Spoon the mixture into muffin tins lined with paper cups, filling them 3/4 full. Bake the cupcakes in a preheated moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and crusty on the surface.
Yield: 12 cupcakes.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise. Fold in all other ingredients.
Pour into large dish and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: potato quiche
directions: Slice potatoes and cook in pressure cooker until done.
Mix soup, sour cream, butter and onion.
Pour this mixture over potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Gently stir.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all
together.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan or muffins.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375° or if you have been baking and oven is already hot.

title: macaroni supreme
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add chicken, cut up in chunks, bouillon and garlic; stir-fry until chicken is brown.
Remove chicken.
In same skillet, add 2 tablespoons of butter and add onion, yellow pepper, carrots, broccoli, tarragon leaves and lemon pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Mix with the macaroni.
Add the chicken. Stir in cheese until cheese melts.
Blend flour and milk and stir into mixture.

title: basic banana pudding
directions: Combine flour and 2/3 cup of sugar in saucepan.
Mix well. Stir in milk and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cover bottom of an 8-inch lightly greased (spray with cooking spray) baking dish with a layer of vanilla wafers.
Top with half the bananas and half of the pudding.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add cream of tartar, then gradually the sugar, continuing to beat until whites hold a peak but are not dry.
Spread evenly over pudding, sealing to the edge of the baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in slices.
Put in pan with 1/2 cup water and 1/2 stick butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender and drain.
Mix bread crumbs, beaten egg and sugar, then add to cooked squash.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover top with cheese. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: zesty tacos
directions: Step 1:
Brown your ground meat 5 to 6 minutes in water.

title: spinach spaghetti
directions: Mix sour cream and
spinach
together, then mix in with cooked spaghetti.	Mix in remaining ingredients, except grated Jack cheese.
Put in 13	x 9-inch glass pan. Add grated cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender.

title: bessie's picnic layer cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar together.
Blend in eggs or egg substitute (Egg Beaters, Scramblers, etc.).
Blend in dry ingredients, alternating with applesauce.
Fold in raisins and nuts.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Add flour mixture and shortening to buttermilk mixture.
Drop batter by spoonfuls onto hot griddle or heavy iron skillet.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate and water in double boiler.
When melted, stir in powdered sugar and add butter, bit by bit.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes.
Gently fold in chocolate; reheat slightly to melt chocolate, if necessary.
Stir in rum and vanilla.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, soup and sour cream together.
Melt margarine and mix dressing mix until all the margarine is absorbed in mix.
Pour 1/2 dressing mix into squash mixture and mix well.
Pour into large casserole and place rest of dressing mix on top.
Cook for 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients
Cut in shortening; add buttermilk.
Knead dough and roll out to 3/4 inch thickness.
Cut out and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.
Biscuits may be brushed with melted butter before baking.

title: japanese crepes
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add egg and milk and mix well.
Add melted butter.
