Cover the bottom of a smooth frying pan with oil. Add a very thin layer of batter, just covering the bottom of the pan.
Don't cook to brownness, but before it gets brown flip the very slim pancake so the other side can cook; then remove and either let cool or not.
To eat, add butter, jam, chocolate, ice cream, rolled up in it.
Makes 5 crepes.

title: meal in one
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain.
Add corn, green beans and tomato sauce.
Mix well and heat until hot.
Spray or butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with rolls or biscuits.
Put 3 to 4 layers of mixture, then cheeses, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: light dessert
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, toss gently. Spoon fruit mixture into a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set dish aside.
Combine flour, sugar and nutmeg in a small bowl.
Add oil, with a fork, stir until all dry ingredients are moistened and mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle topping over fruit mixture.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until topping is lightly browned.
Yields 8 servings, 180 calories per serving and 3.7 g fat.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Heat sour cream, prepared mustard and 1/2 teaspoon salt to serve as a sauce over the meatballs.
Do not allow sauce to boil.

title: walnut grape salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and marmalade, mixing until well blended.
Add grapes and celery and mix lightly; cover.
Chill, stir in walnuts just before serving.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in small mixer bowl.
Flake shrimp over cream cheese and mix.
Set in refrigerator about 1/2 hour, then form into ball.

title: creamy chicken pasta bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix soup, sour cream, pepper and 1 cup of the cheese.
Toss with pasta.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange chicken breasts over pasta mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cup cheese and seasoning.
Bake 40 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dahl
directions: Vary proportions to suit taste.

title: dill crackers
directions: Stir 10 minutes until dry, then marinate overnight.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: In a small saucepan, bring water, corn syrup, and sugar to a simmer over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Remove pan from heat and add chocolate, swirling pan to submerge chocolate in hot syrup.
Let chocolate stand in syrup 2 minutes, and whisk until smooth.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients except butter and cinnamon until it crumbles and sprinkle over apples.
Pour melted butter over all and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Measure sugar, corn syrup and peanut butter into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until peanut butter melts and mixture is well blended.
Remove from heat.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine wet ingredients and mix well. Incorporate the dry ingredients into the wet. Put into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 90 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and green pepper together, then drain. Mix with other ingredients and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Stir occasionally.

title: festive egg squares
directions: Layer sausage, mushrooms, green onions, tomatoes and cheese in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Beat remaining ingredients and pour over sausage mixture. Cook, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes or until golden brown and set. Cut into 12 (3-inch) squares.

title: ukha(fish puree)
directions: Boil water, then add carrot, celery, peppercorns, onion, parsnip, leek, bay leaves and salt to taste.
Simmer 15 minutes; add 2 pounds (only) of the fish and cook until it begins to fall apart.
Force this through a sieve; return to the pot, bring to a boil and add remaining 2 pounds of raw fish, which has been sliced.
Cook about 15 minutes; add lemon juice before serving.

title: low-calorie vegetable soup
directions: On stove top in large pot, heat tomatoes and water, bring to boil.

Add bouillon, onion, carrots, cabbage, parsley and celery. Simmer approximately 20 minutes until carrots and celery cooked. Add frozen vegetables and simmer another 10 to 15 minutes and serve when ready.

title: crawfish etoufee
directions: Place oil in a Dutch oven.
Season crawfish tails generously with Creole seasoning and salt and pepper.
Add paprika to vegetable oil.
Saute crawfish tails about 5 minutes.
Remove tails and set aside.
To pot, add chopped onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute well for at least 10 minutes.
Return crawfish tails to pot and add Worcestershire sauce and 2 cups water.
Stir and simmer 40 minutes.
Check taste; add more seasoning, if needed.
Add mixture of cornstarch and water slowly until thick. Serve over rice.
Garnish with green onion and parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: leftovers casserole
directions: Using a deep casserole dish, slice half the potatoes and layer on the bottom.
Layer corn over them, including juice if any.
Add a layer of diced onion, then a layer of ham, followed by a layer of peas.
Finish by layering remaining potatoes on top.
Add enough milk (with salt stirred in) to barely come to top of vegetables. If you wish, you can first thicken milk with a little flour (1 tablespoon) before adding.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix sugar with the cream as it is whipped. Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell. Chill.

title: basic sweet dough(for bread or cinnamon rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar
in water.
Scald milk, add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool
to
lukewarm
and add 2 cups flour.
Beating with electric mixer,
add yeast and eggs. Beat well and add remainder of flour
to
make
a
soft dough. Knead lightly and
place
in
greased bowl.
Cover and set in warm place and
let
rise
until
double in bulk.
When light, punch down and shape into rolls or buns.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix graham cracker crumbs in and pat down.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips, then coconut, then nuts.
Pour milk on top. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until light brown.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
In sauce pan stir sugar and corn starch together until mixed.
Add vinegar and beet juice and stir well.
Stir over low heat until thickened and clear.
Add beets and butter.
Reheat and serve.

title: cherry delight
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. With mixer, beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together until light.
Add to whipped Dream Whip and blend well by hand.
Spread over cake pieces.
Lift cake pieces with fork so cream cheese mixture gets down around cake pieces.
Chill for 2 hours.
Spread cherry pie filling over all and chill 2 or 3 more hours.

title: peach delight
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in water.
Heat in a small saucepan until mixture clears.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour ice cold water, milk powder and almond extract into a chilled bowl.
Beat at high speed until the mixture is thick, about 10 minutes.
Beat cooled gelatin into the whipped milk.
Fold in peaches, honey and walnuts and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Top with cracker crumbs.

title: lebanese lentils
directions: Put olive oil in iron frying pan.
When hot, place onions until blackened.
In separate pot, put remaining ingredients.
Add onions to pot.
Rinse frying pan with small amount of water; add to pot. Bring to boil with high heat, then lower to medium-low heat.
Cook on slow heat until well done, approximately 1 hour.
Serve with salad and pita bread.

title: "hawaiian chicken"
directions: Brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: refrigerator pan rolls
directions: Combine hot water, sugar, salt and margarine; stir well.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine water mixtures, egg and 2 1/2 cups of flour, beat until smooth.
Add enough flour (about 2 3/4 cups) to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board, knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover tightly, store in refrigerator until doubled or needed.
(May be kept 4 to 5 days.) Punch dough down, form small balls, place on greased pan.
Cover, let rise in warm place until doubled (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Roll into small balls, using prongs of fork press into patty.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter; add flour and blend together until smooth.
Add milk gradually, constantly stirring until mixture boils.
Add salt and pepper; cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in grated cheese and add the macaroni, or put in baking dish or casserole.
Sprinkle with additional grated cheese and bake at 400° until golden brown.
A few strips of bacon, placed on top a few minutes before baking is complete is a good addition.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with butter.
Place onion, asparagus, cracker crumbs, soup, egg and margarine in baking dish.
Cook until onion is cooked.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: baked onions
directions: Beat eggs and add to sauce.
Season to taste.
In well-greased baking dish slice very thin half onions.
Cover with sauce and cheese.
Add remaining sliced onions and sauce.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes until onions are tender.
Remove from oven and top with remaining cheese.
Return to oven until cheese bubbles.

title: sweet chunk pickles
directions: Clean cukes and chunk into 1-inch pieces.
Soak overnight in 1 cup salt and 1 gallon vinegar.
In the morning, drain and boil in 2 quarts water and 2 cups vinegar until they lose their bright green color.
Drain.
Put alum size of pea in each pint.
Make syrup of 6 cups brown sugar and 2 cups white sugar, 4 cups vinegar, 3 tablespoons allspice berries, 2 tablespoons celery seed and 8 sticks of cinnamon.
Heat slowly to boiling point and pour over pickles.
Seal.

title: butter barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter, add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
If stored in fridge, warm before using.
Makes 1 cup.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix with cream mixture.
Add apples.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: corn and cottage cheese casserole
directions: Brown turkey, onion, green pepper and garlic in skillet. Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, cinnamon, oregano and pepper to meat mixture.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add corn to mixture after the simmer time.
Place ingredients into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: slaw mix
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, mustard and sugar.
Add to shredded cabbage.
You can double the recipe if you like more Slaw Mix.

title: chicken salad
directions: Clean and wash the chicken and put into either a crock-pot or a roaster pan.
Cook on high if using a crock-pot, 300° if baking in oven.
Cool and chop into medium size pieces.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and mash.
Add margarine, cheese, egg, onion, milk and 3/4 cup cracker crumbs.
Put into buttered dish and sprinkle top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Fry and drain meats.
Combine meats, oregano and salts.
Cook cheese until melted and add to meat mixture.
Blend well.
Spread on party rye.
Freeze on cookie sheet until set.
Place in baggies in freezer until ready to use.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with onion.
In a separate bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients; pour over chops.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a small bowl.
Sift all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening; add buttermilk, then yeast mix.
Stir until thoroughly moistened.
Knead a minute or two.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Cut into rounds.
Brush with melted butter and bake on an ungreased pan at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Dough may be refrigerated until ready to use.
It will keep for several days.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flour, eggs, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Cook until thickened over medium heat.
Mix with macaroni. Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Add mandarin oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well. Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: old family casserole
directions: Saute chopped onions and green pepper in shortening.
Add hamburg and fry just until meat is slightly cooked in loose pieces. Do not brown.
Add the milk and soup; stir gently. Alternately layer first the hamburg mixture, then grated potatoes and salt and pepper in a well-greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Finish with a layer of hamburg.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix the pudding mix and pineapple, then add Cool Whip, marshmallows and 1 cup of nuts to mix.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix all together, put in bowl, cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Mix once or twice during the time it is marinating.

title: open-faced broiler sandwiches
directions: Spread bread with mayonnaise.
Add some turkey, chicken or roast beef.
Place cooked broccoli and cover with yellow or white cheese (your favorite).
Broil until cheese melts.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, lemon juice, basil, lite salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Add remaining ingredients and toss together.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture forms soft ball when tested in 1/2 cup cold water.
Remove from heat and fold in the peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into 12-inch square pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef cubes.
Add diced up potatoes, celery, onions and carrots on top of beef cubes.
Mix soups as directed on the cans.
Pour that over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old timey chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix the sugar and cocoa together.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook on low heat until the sugar melts and the mixture is smooth.
Turn up the heat to medium-high and cook until it reaches a soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat with a WOODEN spoon over a pan of cold water until the mixture loses its gloss and thickens.
Pour into a lightly buttered dish.

title: candy bar
directions: Cover a 9 x 13-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Put a layer of saltines on the bottom.
Bring sugar and butter to a boil, boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 4 minutes (watch carefully not to burn).
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Cool.

title: economy chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, soda and cocoa; add to vinegar, vanilla, oil and water.
Stir together; don't beat.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate mallow pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/2 c. of milk until smooth.
Add pudding mix and remaining milk; mix well.
Fold in marshmallows. Pour into crust.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix yeast, milk and sugar in a large bowl.
Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes.
With fork, beat in oil, eggs and salt.
With spoon, beat in 2 cups flour.
Add 2 cups flour and beat 2 minutes, until mixture forms a soft ball.
Add remaining 1/2 cup flour if dough is too soft to handle.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Split Twinkies and place 1 layer in pan.
Pour in pudding mix with milk (according to directions).
Add a layer of drained crushed pineapple, then a layer of sliced bananas.
Follow with another layer of Twinkies.
Ice with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut, pecans and cherries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peach muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and beat well. Beat vanilla and sour cream or yogurt into creamed mixture.
Add flour and baking powder.
Stir well.
Add chopped peaches and pecans just until mixed.

title: oven fried chicken with dressing
directions: Season chicken to taste and fry in hot fat.
Combine bread crumbs, salt, pepper, sage, onions and butter, using 1/2 cup of soup.
Arrange chicken in Dutch oven.
Pile dressing in center. Make gravy of pan drippings, using 2 tablespoons flour and enough water with remaining soup to make 2 cups.
Pour over chicken, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: In pan, mix egg yolks, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Add mayonnaise and mustard. Boil potatoes with skin on.
When done, peel skins off and cut into large bite size pieces.
In large bowl, lightly toss potatoes, celery, onions and dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate 4 hours to overnight.
The longer it sets, the better it is.

title: old fashioned cookies
directions: Stir with a spoon.
Roll out by hand or roll into a ball.
Bake at 450°; cook until lightly browned.

title: blackberry pie with dumplings
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Mix together with shortening and margarine until it resembles meal. Mix enough buttermilk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on counter until thin.
Boil berries, sugar and water.
Cut dough into small dumplings.
Drop into boiling berries and cook for about 5 minutes. Let stand about 10 minutes in juice before serving.
This is really good with vanilla milk poured over it.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Combine tomatoes, sauce, puree, mushrooms, onions and meat. Cook 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Layer in baking dish first ingredients (sauce) and spaghetti.
Add cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: cooked soap
directions: Dissolve lye in water and let stand until it is lukewarm. Add slowly to the fat, stirring constantly until jelly-like. Cool slowly.
Add Borax and water and mix thoroughly.
Remove from fire.
Add ammonia and stir until thick like honey.
Pour into mold.
Cut and let cure for 4 to 6 weeks.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375 for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Brown chicken in margarine until golden on both sides in large skillet.
Add soup, milk and onion.
Simmer 1 hour, covered, or a little more until chicken is done.
Stirring several times, add more milk if needed so there is ample gravy.
Great with potatoes or egg noodles.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain on paper towels.
Beat eggs; add milk, dry mustard and salt.
In bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan, spread bread cubes and top with sausage.
Sprinkle cheese and pour on egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cover with foil the last 15 or 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a baked pie shell. Sprinkle with crushed peanuts.
Chill.

title: chocolate-caramel decadence
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
While it is still warm, poke holes in cake with fork.
Combine milk and caramel topping and pour over the top of cake.
Refrigerate.
When cool, frost cake with Cool Whip and top with crushed candy bars.
Cut into bars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the first 7 ingredients as listed.
Mix sugar, seasoned salt and garlic powder and sprinkle over top of mayonnaise. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
When ready to eat, cook 1/2 pound of bacon and crumble on top.
Slice boiled eggs and put on top of bacon.

title: "bana pancakes"
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix until just combined. Heat griddle.
Spray with cooking spray.

title: harvard beets
directions: Bring to boil; pour over cooked beets and refrigerate overnight.

title: japanese cabbage salad
directions: Put shredded cabbage and bean sprouts into large bowl.
Add mushrooms, onions and sunflower seeds.
Add toasted almonds and sesame seed.
Combine broken noodles and chow mein noodles in small bowl, set aside.

title: old fashioned bread dressing
directions: Buns should be quite dry.
Leave out overnight or dry out in a slow oven (250°).
Crumble buns into a large bowl.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in bananas, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and stir just until well combined.
Spread batter into two greased and floured loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/3-inch).
Bake in a 350° oven until tests done with wooden pick (50 to 60 minutes).
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix Velveeta, Ro-Tel and soup in dish in microwave until creamy.
Cook egg noodles until almost done.
Mix everything together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and set aside.
In a covered saucepan, on medium heat, cook soup mix, rice and water for 7 minutes.
Combine sausage, soup and rice mixture, pepper, onion, celery and almonds. Place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef in large soup pot.
Drain fat.
Add all ingredients, except for beans and macaroni.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add beans and macaroni; cook until done.
This freezes very nicely!

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine ingredients and press into pie shell.
Let sit 1/2 hour before filling.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Crush candy bars.
Mix Cool Whip, marshmallow cream and Eagle Brand milk.
Add 1 cup milk.
Add candy bars.
Pour into ice cream maker and fill to the fill line with additional milk.

title: roadhouse potatoes
directions: Heat cream and butter.
Add salt.
Place potatoes in flat, greased glass 9 x 12-inch dish.
Pour cream mixture over potatoes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350°.
Can put in tube pan or flat pan.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion in a large stock pot.
Add other ingredients and cook slowly for about an hour.
If tangy, add a touch of sugar.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to package directions and set aside. Melt butter in heavy saucepan. Saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute over low heat. Add mushrooms, broth and half and half.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in rice, chicken, pimento, parsley and seasonings.
Pour mixture into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Top with pecans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add egg, then flour and remaining ingredients.
Make 2 log-type rolls about 1 1/2-inch in diameter. Put in refrigerator or freezer.
(Can be kept for days.)
Slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: special k treats
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute.
Measure peanut butter and cereal in large bowl. Mix carefully, trying not to crush cereal.
Pour corn syrup, sugar mixture over cereal and peanut butter; stir quickly to cover cereal.
Place into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; spread evenly.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Drop by one full tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
When completely cool, ice with the icing.

title: quick and easy fudge brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate and butter.
Microwave at High (100%) for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.
Add sugar; stir with spoon until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and nuts, if desired.
Stir until wooden pick inserted in center comes out almost clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Frost with Quick and Easy Chocolate Frosting, if desired.
Cut into squares. Makes about 24 brownies.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar gradually beating until very light.
Add 1 egg at a time beating well after each egg.
Add flavor and beat well.
Turn into greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail parfait pie
directions: Drain fruit; save syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup. Heat to boiling.
Add jello; dissolve.
Add cold water and ice cream (cut into pieces).
Stir until melted.
Chill until mixture thickens.
Fold into fruit.
Turn into vanilla cookie crust.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Flake with a fork.
Add lemon juice, 1/2 cup corn flakes and white sauce, stirring well.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Shape into croquettes.
Roll in remaining corn flakes. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in preheated through quart saucepan.
Brown over medium heat long enough to render out some chicken fat.
Remove chicken.
Reduce heat to low.
Add onion and stir briefly (1 to 2 minutes).
Do not brown.
Return chicken to pan and add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low.
Simmer and cook 30 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Cool.
Discard skin and bones.
Dice chicken and return to pan.
Soup can be refrigerated for future use at this time.
Just before serving, return soup to boil; add noodles and cook 8 minutes.

title: sausage biscuits balls
directions: Mix Bisquick, water, and sausage well.
Then add the grated cheese and mix well.
Roll into large marble size
balls.
Bake at 350°
until brown.
May be made in advance and refrigerated or placed in the freezer.

title: pineapple chiffon cake
directions: Beat butter like whipped cream.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavorings, flour and baking powder, alternately with the milk.
Bake at 325°.

title: garbage dip
directions: Chop first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine and refrigerate 8 hours at least.

title: streamlined bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add 1/2 of flour, oil, sugar and salt.
Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Then add the other half of flour.
Mix with spoon until blended.
Cover bowl and put in warm place (85°) for 30 minutes, until doubles.
Mix with spoon 25 strokes; pour into greased pan.
Smooth dough by patting with floured hand.
Let rise 45 minutes until 1/2-inch from top of pan. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Tap top of loaf.
It should sound hollow.
Take from pan immediately and brush top with butter.
Serves 12.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool somewhat and add frozen orange juice, stirring to melt.
Chill until slightly syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into rectangular glass pan, about 7 x 12-inch.
Chill and serve.

title: mashed potato filling
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Pour over bread cubes.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and potatoes.
Add to bread.
Add milk and mix.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: simple stroganoff
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef with onion until beef is browned. Drain fat off in colander and return to skillet.
Add beef broth, soup and water.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Reduce to low heat. Add noodles and sour cream.
Simmer 19 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool until partially congealed. Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold; chill until firm. Pretty served with carrot curls and radish roses.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix the pasta with the cubed cheese, broccoli, carrots, pepperoni and olives.
Add salad dressing to taste.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook sausage until done and drain.
In a large casserole dish, place corn, cracker crumbs and eggs which have been beaten with milk, onion, butter and cooked sausage.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to an hour until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: tossed salad for six
directions: Place egg yolk in bowl rubbed with garlic.
Mash with spoon; combine seasonings, stir in vinegar and salad oil, chopped egg white; add parsley and beat well.
Add onion slices, spinach and lettuce that have been chopped.
Toss and serve.

title: "daffodillies"
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Separate dough into 12 pieces.
Using kitchen scissor, cut rolls from outside, almost to center, to form 8 petals.
Place on prepared cookie sheet. Make
deep indention in center of each roll, using end of wooden spoon or thumb.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, butter, mustard and dill weed.
Mix until smooth.
Fill centers of rolls with heaping teaspoonful of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly; refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese bread
directions: Split bread in half lengthwise and place on a large baking sheet.
Butter each half generously.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and onions in a small mixing bowl.
Mix well, then spread on bread until all mixture is used.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.
It should be brown and bubbly.
Let cool slightly before slicing.

title: fudge
directions: In double boiler, melt butter and cheese.
In a large bowl, put sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Pour melted mixture into sugar. Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread into two 9 x 13-inch pans and cool.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix jello with water as directed; add salt.
Put in an 8-inch square pan.
Let soft-set, then add pineapple and carrots.

title: adam and eve cake(apple and fig cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Bundt pan at 300° to 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Add Coke, cream cheese and remaining ingredients.
Chill in a mold.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Mix together.
Let simmer in crock-pot for 2 hours.

title: spanish carrots
directions: Heat butter in pan and brown lightly.
Add onions and garlic and fry until slightly brown. Add carrots, water, ketchup and chili powder. Cook on medium heat until carrots are just crispy. Add strips of pepper the last 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Pour in pie shell. Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: mexican cold dip
directions: Spread bean dip in bottom of dish.
Mash avocados and layer on top of beans.
Mix together sour cream, mayo, lemon juice and taco mix and spread over avocado layer.
Chop green onions and sprinkle on top of sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle black olives on top of onions.
Chop tomato.
Drain the juice and sprinkle on top of the olives.
Grate Cheddar cheese and add.

title: microwave tapioca pudding
directions: Fill small paper cups with apple juice and freeze partially; insert a popsicle stick in each and freeze until firm.
Peel away paper cups and enjoy a good, natural and nutritious snack.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and let it set in the refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, dissolve jello in hot water.
When mixture begins to set, add it to the cranberry mixture, then add the remaining ingredients.
Stir all together. Put in a large bowl and refrigerate.
It will keep up to 2 weeks or can be frozen.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: cauliflower and longhorn quiche
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets, rinse and cut into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Steam until crisp-tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water; drain on paper towels.
Toast almonds on shallow pan in 350° oven for 8 minutes (if desired).
In blender, combine eggs, milk, mayonnaise, 1/4 cup of cheese, pepper and nutmeg; blend until smooth.
Place cauliflower in bottom of pie shell and sprinkle with almonds.
Pour filling mixture over cauliflower. Sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup cheese.
Bake on bottom rack of 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
This can also be made with Brussels sprouts.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In a soup kettle or Dutch oven, melt butter. Stir in flour. Heat and stir until smooth. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add potatoes and onions. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Add bacon, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper. Stir until cheese is melted.

title: board supper meat loaf
directions: Mix 1 can soup with other ingredients. Divide into 2 loaves. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with second can soup.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: ice box pie
directions: Mix egg yolk, beaten, milk and lemon juice. Beat well and pour in pie shell.
Then beat egg whites with about 1/4 c. sugar.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Combine all ingredients. Place in casserole dish and bake at 375° until bubbly hot.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix eggs, milk and flour.
Fold in ham, cheese, onion and seasonings.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 4.

title: thick chili
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add other ingredients and cook for at least 2 1/2 hours. Add water as needed.
Remember if the spoon will not stand up in the pot, it's too thin.

title: nut roll
directions: In large mixing bowl mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeaat.

title: chocolate pecan pie bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. In large bowl mix at medium speed flour, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and salt
until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; press firmly and evenly into pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach casserole(microwave)
directions: Mix in large microwavable bowl; cover.
Cook on High for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pat-a-pizzas
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Season with oregano, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Press biscuits flat on cookie sheet.
Spoon pizza sauce onto biscuits.
Place in oven.
Cook until biscuits are golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Spoon beef onto biscuits. Place one slice of cheese on each biscuit.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: "shake 'n bake" coating mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.

title: spicy beef stew
directions: Brown meat slowly in
Dutch
oven
with
oil.
Sprinkle with sugar and brown until
well
seared.
Dust with flour and continue to brown.
Add
seasonings,
bay
leaf, cloves, tomatoes, chopped onion and
green
pepper.
Add broth, V-8 juice, Tabasco sauce and dried whole
red pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until
meat
is tender.
Remove red pepper. Add vegetables except peas
and
simmer
30 minutes.
Add peas and simmer 15 minutes. Serve with baking powder biscuits.

title: baby food pound cake
directions: Beat 3 eggs. Add and beat 2 cups sugar. Add cooking oil, sifted flour, allspice, cinnamon, nutmeg and apricot baby food. Stir in vanilla and chopped pecans. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in a tube pan. Let cool 30 minutes; while still warm, mix 1 cup 4x sugar and juice and rind of 1 lemon. Pour over cake.

title: green chile chicken
directions: In a skillet, saute onions and green chilies in butter.
Add mushroom soup and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add noodles and chicken. Top with cheese.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: west indies salad
directions: Layer crab meat and onion in bowl. Pour remaining ingredients over, 1 at a time. Marinate from 2 to 12 hours.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and baking powder together.
Cream margarine, sour cream and eggs together.
Mix both mixtures together well; add vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is golden brown and shrinks from pan sides.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Heat; serve on vegetables or with Mexican food.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef with onion, salt and pepper to taste and butter.
Add chopped hot dogs when beef is just about completely browned.

title: fish topped with wine and vegetables
directions: Combine
bulgur
and
bouillon
granules
in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish and pour boiling water over the top.
Place fish
on top,
tucking under
any
thin edges.
Sprinkle with garlic
salt and basil.
Place frozen vegetables and tomato on top
of
fish; drizzle with wine.
Cover tightly with foil and bake
in
a preheated
oven
for 25 to 30 minutes (fish should flake easily with fork).
Makes 2 servings.

title: kolaches(fruit filled pastry)
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, salt and eggs thoroughly.
Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat 5 minutes at low on electric mixer.
Stir in remaining flour.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and turn out on lightly floured board.
Makes 1-inch balls.
Cover and let rise 10 minutes. Press down centers and fill with pie filling (cherry, peach, prune, apricot).
Let rise 25 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the 3 pieces of chicken; pick off bone and cool.
Fix soups together plus 1 can water.
Add 1 stick of margarine to soups.
Place in dish as follows:
(1) layer of stuffing, (2) layer of chicken, (3) layer of soups, (4) layer of stuffing.
Repeat until all used up.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: steak and mushroom bits
directions: Brown steak and 2 tablespoons oil in skillet; drain.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil and the next 4 ingredients.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Cook for 1 minute.
Stir in bouillon cube; dissolve in boiling water and remaining ingredients.
Bring it to a boil; simmer, covered, for 2 minutes.
Add steak.
Cook until steak is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: scallops provencale
directions: Rinse and pat dry scallops.
Brown scallops lightly in butter in a large frying pan, removing them as they brown and dividing evenly into 4 buttered baking shells or shallow individual casseroles.
In same pan, cook onion and mushrooms until onion is soft and begins to brown.
Mix in garlic, tomatoes, wine, catsup, salt, tarragon, rosemary and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Uncover; reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook until thick, about 3 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and vinegar until well combined.
Spoon sauce evenly over scallops.
Bake at 400° until sauce bubbles and begins to brown at edges, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Cook roast until very tender.
Chop meat.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over meat in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve in buns.

title: mock cheese cake(this recipe is an easy project for children.)
directions: Using a wooden spoon, mix instant vanilla pudding and sour cream until smooth.
Pour over pie crust.
Add fruit pie filling on top and refrigerate a couple of hours or overnight.
Do not freeze.

title: mulligatawny soup(compliments of sylvia's rigdon hall, cambria)
directions: Bring water to a boil; add chicken.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from stock; refrigerate stock to clean off fat.
When cool, remove skin and bones from chicken; pull or cut into bite size chunks.
Add next 8 items to reheated, defatted chicken stock.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Cream peanut butter with cream cheese.
Add alternately sugar and 2/3 of Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell. Spread remainder of Cool Whip on top and chill before serving.

title: tuna pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine cheeses and onion and put in bottom of pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender for 15 seconds or by hand for 1 minute.
Pour over ingredients in baking pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
You also can substitute shrimp or crabmeat.

title: bean dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave. Mix together well the refried beans, cream cheese, Ro-Tel, sour cream, 3/4 shredded cheese and green chiles. Garnish with jalapeno slices. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Spread extra shredded cheese. Bake until melted.

title: spicy ramen
directions: Boil Ramen noodles until done.
Add seasoning that comes with Ramen noodles.
Put 1 teaspoon mustard and hot sauce to taste. Add crumbled sausage.
Mix and enjoy!

title: potato candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add more powdered sugar, if necessary, and mix until stiff enough to roll out.
Roll into a rectangle, spread top with peanut butter and roll as for jelly roll.
Chill.
Slice and serve.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
In small bowl, make a paste of cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water.
Pour mixture into broth.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Mixture should be thickened and translucent.
Reduce heat.
Add eggs, a little at a time, stirring to separate into ribbons.
Garnish with onion.
Serve immediately.

title: zesty pecans
directions: Melt butter and A.1. sauce; mix in pecans.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake 1 1/2 hours at 200°, stirring once or twice during cooking time.
Spread out on brown paper; sprinkle with salt.

title: cheddar bacon toasts
directions: In a bowl, combine the cheese, mayonnaise and bacon. Cut the bread into 24 slices about 1/2-inch each. Spread the cheese mixture on one side of each slice. Place on a baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 2 dozen.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken, simmering for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Microwave broccoli and drain.
Arrange broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Combine soup, milk and cheese and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together put in a greased pan.
Bake about 30 minutes to get hot through.
It's a good dish to cook in a crock-pot.

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Simmer for 30 minutes, or until tender. Mix soup with milk and corn; add to vegetables.
Crush tomatoes and add.
Pinch cheese up and slowly add, stirring constantly after cheese is added or it will scorch.
Cook for about 20 minutes.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. After cool, take cake and punch holes throughout with fork.
Mix Jell-O of your choice as directed on package and pour over cake. Put in refrigerator overnight.
Spread Cool Whip over cake (thickness of your choice).
Cut and serve.

title: cheesecake
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until
fluffy.
Beat in milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes; cool.
Spread sour cream on top; chill.

title: quick beef and noodle dish
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Mix ground beef with noodles and add soup and water. Cook on medium heat until hot.
Serves 8.

title: crab stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add stuffing mix, 1/2 cup undiluted mushroom soup, crab, lemon juice, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Sprinkle inside of chicken breasts with salt. Spoon stuffing down center of each breast; roll up and fasten with metal skewers.

title: fresh vegetable pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar; shake well until creamy.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk to a full boil. Cook 1 1/2 minutes. Add oatmeal and stir 1 to 2 minutes. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Add chopped pecans and drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: date dainties
directions: Cream together sugars and margarine; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture. Add dates and cherries.
Bake at 350° in 10 x 15-inch pan (no smaller).

title: lasagne noodle hot dog
directions: Combine pizza sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles. Split hot dogs and stuff with Mozzarella cheese, then wrap with a noodle.
Place seam side down in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over the top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oriental fried rice
directions: Saute green pepper, celery, carrot and green onion in vegetable oil until vegetables are tender.
Add cooked rice. Stir in soy sauce, garlic salt and pepper.
In separate pan, scramble the 2 eggs in small amount of oil with 2 tablespoons of soy sauce. Fold the egg mixture and the green peas into the rice mixture and toss lightly.
Add additional soy sauce to taste.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine the ingredients and press onto the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until crust just begins to brown.
Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix the remaining ingredients together with the broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heathman restaurant's rosemary chicken salad sandwich
directions: Place chicken breasts in a pot with just enough water to cover plus 1 coarsely chopped stalk celery, peppercorns, onion, bay leaf and 2 sprigs fresh rosemary.
Poach for 20 minutes.
Reserve a little liquid to use later.
After chicken is cooled and chopped, mix the remaining ingredients with half of the mayonnaise and a little of the poaching water.
Add more mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Serve on lettuce leaves or will make 4 sandwiches on whole wheat bread.

title: aunt rosie's bean salad
directions: Put undrained can of light red kidney beans (Joan of Arc preferred) in a mixing bowl.
Chop eggs, pickles, and onion.
Add to beans.
Stir in mustard, Miracle Whip, and sweeten to taste. More or less Miracle Whip may be added according to your taste. This salad is best if refrigerated overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish; set aside.
Cook potatoes in boiling salted water.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pat's potatoes
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes, onion and pepper in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Put beef in blender and chop fine.
Put all other ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Add chopped beef.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Toss all ingredients together and let stand for 2 days in refrigerator.
This keeps for weeks and is great on or with hot dogs and makes a nice extra on the buffet table.

title: frosty date balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Stir in water and vanilla. Add flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 300° oven about 20 minutes or until cookies are set but not brown.
While warm, carefully roll in confectioners sugar. Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: Note:
Slice, Sprite or ginger ale may be substituted for lemon-lime.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Add sour cream, baking powder and bananas.
Mix.
Add flour, vanilla and egg whites. Mix.
Bake in 3 layers for 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill and serve.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° in 2 (9-inch) layer pans or 1 (13 x 9-inch) sheet cake pan for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Do not mix ingredients.
In square pan (10-inch), spread pineapple and juice over bottom of pan.
Spread cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Spread cherry filling over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut over cherry filling.
Sprinkle walnuts over coconut.
Cut butter into cubes and place over walnuts, about 1/2 inch apart. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: stew 'n' cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Empty beef stew into a shallow 2-quart baking dish.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind 1 package Oreo cookies into crumbs. Set aside.
Combine butter, cream cheese and powder sugar together.
Set aside. Combine milk, pudding let set.
Add Cool Whip to pudding and then add the cream cheese mixture.
In a new large
flowerpot, washed very well or a glass bowl, layer Oreo's then pudding mixture, keep layering crumbs, then pudding mixture until all ingredients are used.
Ending with cookie crumbs on the top layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: christmas peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir in mixture of flour, soda and salt.
Shape into balls.
Roll in colored sugars.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Make small hole in center of each ball.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Insert kisses, point side down, into each cookie.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield:
42 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Then add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper by tablespoons.

title: kaiserschmarren - austrian
directions: Beat butter, sugar, egg yolks and salt and then add flour and milk.
Beat egg whites and fold into the dough.

title: tacos
directions: Brown hamburger meat and cut Velveeta into cubes.
Heat tortillas.
Heat Crisco in skillet and fill tortillas with hamburger meat, Velveeta and chopped onions.
Fry on both sides until light brown.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 2 teaspoons cornstarch and ginger.
Toss until well mixed.
In small bowl, mix remaining soy sauce, water, sugar and remaining cornstarch.
Set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons salad oil in Dutch oven or wok.
Add chicken and stir-fry over heat 3 minutes.
Remove. Add remaining salad oil and heat.
Add carrots and onions.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add zucchini and mushrooms.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Return chicken and add soy sauce mixture.
Cook until mixture thickens. Add rice.
Stir-fry a few minutes and serve.
Delicious.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Crush berries slightly.
Put sugar over berries and stir into fruit.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix water and Sure-Jell in a small saucepan.
Bring to a full boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
At once stir into fruit.
Continue stirring 3 minutes.
Immediately ladle into containers, leaving 1/2 inch space at top.
With a damp cloth, wipe any spills from containers. Cover at once with lids.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Store jam in freezer.

title: lime-lemon jello mold
directions: Mix all together.
Put in ring mold and chill.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: cottage cheese bread
directions: Mix all together.
Let rise once and put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: doritos taco chip salad
directions: Add dressing just before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter or margarine in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat and add milk and vanilla.
Sift powdered sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Gradually add to milk mixture, stirring until blended. Stir in peanut butter.
Press mixture into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill and cut into pieces.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: oreo muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients, cut in butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat egg and milk; stir into dry ingredients until just moistened.
Fold in chopped Oreos.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick spray.
Fill 2/3 full with muffin mixture.
Sprinkle topping on top of muffins.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in tin then remove to wire rack. Drizzle glaze over top.

title: peach cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients; pour over the melted butter.
Take large can peaches, including juice; pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Grate cheeses and let set to room temperature.
Mix all together and form 6 balls.
Lay to one side on wax paper. Sprinkle red pepper and a few dashes of cayenne pepper.
Roll cheese balls into cylinders through the pepper.
Store in wax paper and chill before serving.

title: quick mix(like bisquick)
directions: In a large bowl sift together dry ingredients.
Blend well. With pastry blender, cut in shortening until evenly distributed. Mixture will resemble cornmeal in texture.
Put in a large airtight container.
Label.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Use within 4 months.

title: a touch of german
directions: Melt 1/4 stick of the butter in boiling water, along with a pinch of salt and pepper.
Then pour box or package of rigatoni in boiling water.
Also place kielbasa in a separate pan of boiling water.
After noodles are fully cooked, pour in a frying pan with remaining 1/4 stick of butter.
Pour 1/4 cup oregano in pan with the rigatoni.
When kielbasa is fully cooked, slice all of the kielbasa in 1/2-inch round slices and pour in with rigatoni.
Keep stirring rigatoni, mixing the kielbasa in the frying pan.
Then break eggs over top of rigatoni and kielbasa, also stirring until egg is done and mixed in.
Then place cheese on top of mixed dish in 3 different places.
Cover with lid for 30 seconds, allowing the cheese to melt.
Uncover your dish and serve with a nice grilled steak.

title: layer taco dip
directions: Mix refried beans with taco sauce.

title: sunday supper soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and then shape into 24 balls.
Brown meatballs in skillet.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add the washed, hulled strawberries and boil, covered for 3 minutes. Remove and strain through a sieve of colander without pressing and chill.
Just before serving, combine with remaining ingredients. Makes 4 quarts.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Cover and process at high speed until smooth.
Pour into 6-ounce glasses.
Serves 4.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in very large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening and buttermilk; mix well.
Store uncovered in refrigerator.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Blend milk, eggs, butter, brown sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour over bread crumbs in buttered casserole.
Bake at 325° until knife comes clean when inserted into pudding.
Yields 4 servings.

title: barbecued garlic shrimp
directions: You will need 16 bamboo skewers, soaked in water for 30 minutes.

title: no guilt mud pie
directions: Crush SnackWell grahams until fine.
In a large bowl blend crushed grahams, sugar, Quik and liquid Butter Buds.
Press this mixture into a deep dish pie pan that has been sprayed with a nonfat spray.
Pour softened frozen yogurt into the crust.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Once yogurt has hardened, spread fudge topping on top.
Freeze 30 minutes longer.

title: chuck wagon steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces. Salt and pepper each side to taste. Dredge in flour. In large Dutch oven pot, put 3 tablespoons of oil. Brown meat pieces on both sides. When all pieces are brown, drain drippings from pan. Stir soup and 3 tablespoons flour together with remaining drippings. Place meat pieces into pot. Cover with water and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Add water. Stir occasionally. Serve hot with vegetables and a favorite bread. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix together with salad dressing.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix dried onion, water and sugar.
Set aside. Mix cream cheese and
mayonnaise.
Add
onion mixture, then mix chipped beef in real well.	Mold into a ball.

title: streusel mix
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon in a bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in pecans.
Yields about 1 1/3 cups.

title: chicken pie
directions: Follow directions for browning 9-inch pie shell.
Boil chicken and debone.
Drain can of Veg-All.
Place deboned chicken in 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with Veg-All and cream of celery soup. Place Pillsbury pie shell on top and trim edges.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger in pan; drain grease.
Add taco sauce, enchilada sauce, chilies.
Let simmer.
Meanwhile, grate cheese and chop onion.
Fill taco shells with hamburger mixture.
Save a bit.
Put taco shells in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Put a bit of hamburger on bottom around shells.
Add cheese and onion on top. Bake at 425° 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain everything and mix together.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in two.
Wash in warm water and dry.
Mix all ingredients together in large frypan.
Add wings and stir.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Uncover; cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini in small amount of water 3 minutes; drain and cool.
Cut in 1/2 lengthwise; remove pulp, dice and reserve shell. Saute onion in 1/4 cup oil 5 minutes.
Add zucchini pulp and garlic; saute 3 minutes.
Stir in tomato and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix in breadcrumbs, parsley, salt, pepper and basil.
Spoon into zucchini shells.
Place in oiled 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: In unbuttered 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch baking pan, layer broccoli, chicken, bread cubes and cheese.
Combine gravy, milk and pepper. Pour over mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well; let set overnight.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: dumplings
directions: Make up 1 day and refrigerate overnight, or a few hours (covered).
Roll out thin and drop in rolling boiling broth.

title: orange bundt biscuits
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together.
Grease lightly 1 Bundt pan. Preheat oven to 350°.
Push 1 chunk of cream cheese into the side of each biscuit and squeeze shut.
Leave in biscuit shape.
Dip each biscuit in melted butter.
Roll in sugar mixture.
Stand up each biscuit in wheel fashion around bottom of Bundt pan.
All twenty will fit in pan, there will be only 1 roll of biscuits and you will have to hold each up for a little while.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Invert biscuits onto platter with icing of 1 cup sifted powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons orange juice.
May want to let cool. Serve.

title: wesson oil cake(deep, dark chocolate cake)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost as you like.

title: stew
directions: Slice Mexican Velveeta (mild) cheese on top.
(Salt and pepper to taste.)
Cover and heat slowly to steaming until vegetables and meat previously placed in pot are done.
Spicy! Yummy!!!

title: diabetic pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into 12 muffin cups and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream walnutties
directions: Sift
together
flour,
baking
powder,
soda and salt. Blend remaining ingredients.
Add alternately with dry ingredients blending after each addition.
Fold in 1/2 cup walnuts, chopped. Drop
dough
by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets. Dip
bottom of
greased
glass into a mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar
and
1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Flatten each cookie.
Bake at 375° 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.
Makes approximately 7 dozen.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Blend in flour.
Drop batter on lightly greased jelly roll pan; spread evenly.
Mark lightly and drop teaspoon of filling in each square (6 x 4-inch). Bake at 350° until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut squares. Sift powdered sugar over squares while still warm.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water, pineapple and grated carrot.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in cottage cheese and yogurt.
Pour into 6 cup mold. Use a meat loaf pan to make salad in.
Serves about 10 to 12.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Combine the eggs and oil, add the milk and then stir into the dry ingredients until just moistened.
Stir in the berries and bake in a 12-muffin pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let cool for about 5 minutes in the pan before removing.
Let cool on plate, then cover.
Makes 12 very large muffins.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Do not pare cucumbers.
Slice very thin.
Add onions, peppers, garlic and salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly; let stand for 3 hours, then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients; add cucumber mixture and heat just to the boiling point.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: "easy chicken divan"
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender (do not overcook). Place in greased baking dish. Cover with chicken. Place sliced onion and cheese over chicken. Top with soup mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Pour pineapple and marshmallows in large bowl. Let stand overnight stirring often. Add cranberry sauce in blender for 2 to 3 seconds. Add to pineapple mixture. Add nuts. Mix well. Add whip cream. Add sugar gradually until stiff. Fold in fruit mixture. Best when served immediately the juice acid will dissolve cream.

title: white chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Beat butter in with both sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mix.
Stir in morsels.
Make well rounded drops with a spoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° in oven for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: molasses crumb pies
directions: Save 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and put crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Makes 2 large pies.

title: paula's dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or blender, fine (will resemble potting soil).
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar; set aside.
Mix vanilla pudding and egg yolks and cook until thick.
Let cool and stir in cheese mixture; fold in Cool Whip.
Using a 7-inch or 8-inch flower pot, layer cookies with mixtures ending with cookies on top.
Chill and serve with artificial flower in pot.
It's definitely a conversation piece.

title: orange molded salad
directions: Add enough water to pineapple juice to equal 1 cup.
Boil and pour over Jell-O and cream cheese in small bowl.
Beat with electric beater until Jell-O dissolves and cream cheese is blended. Cool in refrigerator while grating carrot and whipping cream.
Fold pineapple into cooled mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and carrot. Pour into 2-quart mold.
Refrigerate until set; overnight preferred.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: tangy citrus chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish coated with no-stick cooking spray.
In a small bowl, combine lemonade, honey, mustard, thyme and lemon juice, mix well.
Pour half over chicken. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and pour remaining sauce on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until meat juices run clear.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw the spinach and squeeze dry. Stir the soup mix, sour cram and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, chopped water chestnuts and green onions. Cover and chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and let stand for 1 hour in a cool place.
Press mix around each cherry and let dry.
Combine chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Heat until melted; cool slightly.
Dip balls in mixture. Place on waxed paper until hard.
Age for 2 weeks (do not refrigerate).
Makes 75 to 100.

title: microwave pecan pralines
directions: Cream brown sugar and whipping cream.
Add syrup.
Microwave on HIGH for 13 minutes.
Add oleo and pecans.
Beat until creamy. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: ham delights
directions: Split the rolls open lengthwise.
(For easier handling, don't pull rolls apart.)
Mix the margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread the tops and bottoms of rolls with the mixture.
Add ham and cheese to the bottom layer of rolls.
Replace the tops of rolls.
Wrap in foil; place in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve the rolls individually. Optional:
You may leave out Worcestershire sauce and use less cheese if you prefer.
You can also use sliced honey deli ham instead of shaved ham.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine both packages of dry pudding mix and add milk.
Beat until thick.
Add banana slices and stir. Fold in Cool Whip.
In serving bowl, layer vanilla wafers in the bottom, then pour on some of the pudding mixture; repeat this 2-step process 2 more times.
The real beauty of this recipe is that it can be made in about 15 minutes and then served.
However, it can be refrigerated and served later.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have sausage and hamburger at room temperature.
Mix in pancake mix, egg and grated cheese with hands.
Form balls the size of a half dollar.
Place balls on cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown. To serve, insert toothpick in each sausage ball.
Arrange on a serving tray.
Makes 24 to 30 balls.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Add flour gradually.
Add vanilla and pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand in oven 10 minutes, then invert onto plate.

title: pecan delights
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until all sugar is dissolved.
Gradually add milk and mix well. Continue cooking until reaches 248° or firm ball stage. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper lined cookie sheets. Chill until firm. Melt chocolate chips and shortening in microwave. Drizzle over clusters.

title: 5-minute double layer chocolate pie
directions: Beat milk, pudding and 1/2 of the whipped topping in medium bowl with wire whisk 1 minute. Mixture will be thick. Spread in the crust. Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer in crust. Enjoy immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve. Garnish as desired. Preparation time: 5 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: grilled herbed chicken
directions: Combine basil, thyme and oregano in a small bowl; set aside. Trim excess fat from chicken.
Rinse chicken with cold water and pat dry.
Place between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Brush surface of chicken with olive oil.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and reserved herbs.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for about 30 seconds after each addition.
Add flour and salt, then add sour cream and mix thoroughly.
Add flavoring, if desired, and pour into a greased and floured pound cake pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for about one hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Add cooked spinach to all the ingredients. Mix well. Refrigerate until chilled enough to shape into walnut size balls. Place on a cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes about 65 balls.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine in the bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Stir in crushed pretzels and spread evenly in bottom of dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: better-than-sex cake(matter of opinion!)
directions: *Add last before mixing.

title: chocolate squares
directions: When the first mixture is cool, place in a mixing bowl.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix soda with flour and add alternately with buttermilk to mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° about 30 minutes.
Cut and ice while warm.

title: homemade ice cream(vanilla)
directions: Pour into freezer.
Add milk to fill line.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onions in thin slices.
Slice butter into thin pieces.
Grease pan.
In 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer potatoes, onion and butter.
Salt and pepper.
Repeat layers until dish is full.
Add milk until dish if half filled.
Cover and cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, bananas, apples, pineapple and raisins.
Mix honey, lemon juice and mayonnaise and mix with first mixture. Makes 6 servings.

title: sue's vegetable spread
directions: Chop all vegetables
fine. Add salt and let sit one hour. Drain well. Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Mix with one cup mayonnaise. Stir in vegetables. Mix well. Add more mayonnaise if needed. Chill well.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper-lined cookie sheets.
Chill.

title: great aunt sade's lemon sponge-cake pie
directions: In a medium bowl, blend sugar and flour very well. Add melted butter and both egg yolks and make paste.
Add salt, lemon zest, lemon juice (grate off zest, then squeeze out juice) and milk, blending well. Beat egg whites stiff and add last.
Pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking for 10 to 20 minutes.
Pie will fall as it cools.
Serve room temperature if possible, otherwise, refrigerate.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until cheese melts.
Serve as a chip dip.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Pour melted margarine in a casserole dish; mix vegetables, celery soup and sour cream.
Put vegetable mixture in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Cover cheese with crushed cheese crackers.
Sprinkle almond slivers over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pan sausage casserole
directions: Roll sausage in medium size patties.
Fry until 1/2 done. Remove to oblong pan and line bottom of pan.
Slice pepper in thin rings.
Slice onions in thin rings and chop celery in small pieces.
Place vegetables in layers over sausage patties.
Dilute cream soups and pour over meat.
Make sure enough water is added to steam the 1/2 cup rice.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken broth.
Drain broccoli and save broth.
Cut up broccoli.

title: old fashioned honey wheat bread
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in medium saucepan until very warm (120° to 130°).
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Combine warm liquid, 2 cups flour and remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
By hand stir in remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead dough on well-floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 2 minutes. Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until light and double in size, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups of water for 20 minutes.
While they are cooking, mix together the sugar, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, ginger, salt, baking soda and flour; set aside.
When raisins have cooked, add to mixture.
Add cold water and Crisco.
Add the dry ingredients, stirring them until well blended.
Since the raisin mixture will still be fairly hot, no real beating is necessary and the cake takes just a matter of minutes to mix.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes or until the cake springs back when touched in the middle.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake and pudding according to directions.
(Use 8-inch round cake pans.)
Allow cake to cool.

title: peanut butter chips and jelly bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg; blend well.
Reserve 1/2 of mixture; press remaining 1/2 in bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread jelly evenly over crust in pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chips over jelly.
Combine remaining crumb mixture with remaining chips; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: microwave chicken breasts diane
directions: Sprinkle the chicken breasts with seasoning of your choice. Heat oil in a large skillet.
Cook chicken over heat for 4 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Transfer to serving platter.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash apples, core and cut into quarters. Melt butter in an 8 x 8 baking dish and spread apples in dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar on apples. Bake uncovered in 325° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until apples are knife tender.

title: turkey patty melts
directions: Spray 12 inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium heat. Cook onion and bell pepper in skillet 6 to 8 minutes, stirring frequently, until tender. Remove from skillet; keep warm. Mix turkey, chili sauce and garlic powder. Shape mixture into 4 patties, each 5 inches in diameter. Cook patties in skillet over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until turkey is no longer pink in center. Top each patty with about 1/4 c. onion mixture; sprinkle with 2 Tbsp. cheese. Cover and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Spread 1 tsp. mayonnaise on each slice toast. Top with each patty.

title: russian tea
directions: Put in container and shake.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put hash browns in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour margarine over hash browns.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread on the top of hash browns.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine; stir in sugar, water and vanilla.
Add flour, cocoa powder and baking powder and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly.
Remove from pan and cut into 8 bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except Parmesan cheese and crescent rolls; mix well.
Set aside. Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Put points toward the outside in a circle with bases overlapping on a greased cookie sheet.
Spoon the filling evenly over the base of the triangles. Fold points of triangles over the filling and tuck under bases of triangles at center of circle.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and salt.
Top with grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Garnish with sliced hard-boiled eggs and parsley.

title: apple butter in the oven
directions: Grind one whole lemon; add with other ingredients in a large roaster.
Cook at 350° for 3 to 4 hours, stirring often, until thick.
Freeze or can in pints.
Water bath for 10 minutes in boiling water.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together sugar, salt, spices, soda and flour.
In separate bowl, whisk together eggs, oil, pumpkin and milk.
Make a well in flour mixture; add egg mixture and nuts. Stir until moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish and cover with mayonnaise mixture.

title: flour tortilla snacks
directions: Blend ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill.
Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces.

title: kahlua mocha fudge
directions: Line bottom of a long Pyrex baking dish (or a small cookie sheet) with foil and set aside.
In a 2-quart pan, combine sugar, butter, milk, Kahlua and coffee.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes and remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread into pan.
Chill until firm.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the unbleached flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, combine the beaten egg, milk and melted margarine; add all at once to flour mixture, stirring until batter is blended, but still slightly lumpy.

title: baba ghannouj
directions: Cut stems off top of eggplants.
Bake on cookie sheet in 550° oven for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter with the brown sugar.
Add the eggs, the corn syrup and the vanilla.
Beat well.
Put your pecans on the bottom of the crust (uncooked).
Pour the first mixture over your pecans and cook 40 minutes at 375°.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix together;
shape into small balls.	Place in casserole and cook
about
minutes at 350°.
Mix sauce and pour over meat balls.
Finish cooking, about 20 minutes.

title: moma b's chili
directions: Brown meat and add onion and celery; cook until onion is slightly cooked.
Add carrots, beans, tomatoes, V-8, salt, pepper and chili powder.
(Couple of dashes of hot sauce, if desired.) Simmer about 1 hour.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine cooked sweet potatoes, butter, salt and pepper; drop 1/3 to 1/2 cup at a time onto crushed cereal flakes which have been spread over waxed paper.
Place each ball on pineapple slice in buttered pan.
Top with maraschino cherry.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: poppy seed bread(cake)
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour and baking powder together.
In a large bowl, mix other ingredients, except poppy seed.
Put flour mix and then poppy seed in last.
Mix 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 2 quart pan mix together above ingredients.
