Cook over medium heat until brittle in cold water (like hard candy, spin a thread) or nuts start to turn dark.
Turn fire out.
Add soda and stir until foam almost settles.
Pour out on greased pan; cool and break.

title: chili-cheese chicken in black bean sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350`.
Using a small sharp knife, make a deep pocket the length of each chicken piece by cutting between the tenderloin and top portion of meat.
Be careful not to cut entirely through the meat.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and stir in mayo.

title: liver dumpling soup from karl ratzsch's
directions: To make dumplings, saute onion in butter until translucent. Add salt, pepper, bases and marjoram.
Let cool.
In large bowl, place cooled onion mixture, liver, eggs, suet, cracker meal and flour and combine, using paddles.
Shape into dumplings with small scoop and drop into boiling stock.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine sausage, cheese and biscuit mix until dough forms a ball.
Pinch off pieces and roll into bite-size balls.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet and bake in 350°
oven for 20 minutes or until bottoms are golden brown.
Stick colored toothpicks in them and serve warm.

title: lasagna
directions: In a 13 x 15-inch dish, layer noodles, sausage, Ricotta, hamburg, sauce and shredded cheeses.
Place layer of noodles between each ingredient.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Cook the vegetables and noodles; drain.
Mix with the remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot until hot.

title: salmon rolls
directions: Roll biscuit dough to 1/4-inch thickness on floured board. Combine salmon, onion, green pepper and salt.
Moisten slightly with salmon liquid.
Mix well and spread mixture on dough.
Roll as for jelly roll and slice 1 1/2 inches thick.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil.
Stir until dry or softened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: south of the border crepe
directions: Use
1 flour
tortilla	per
person.
Butter
tortilla. Sprinkle with cinnamon
and sugar.	Cook tortilla until butter or margarine is melted,
about 15 seconds in a microwave.
Add 1 dip of ice cream on top and serve.

title: redenbacher's ribbon o'fudge bars
directions: In a large Dutch oven, over low heat, melt marshmallows with butterscotch chips and butter; stir occasionally until smooth. Add popcorn; toss until well coated.

title: soy base soy milk
directions: Blend until smooth the soy base, water, salt, honey and vanilla on low speed in oil and 3 more cups of water.
Chill and serve.

title: orange salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on box.
When Jell-O has jelled in refrigerator completely, mix remaining ingredients.
Cut and fold into mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease 1 quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients, except enough cracker crumbs to cover top of casserole.
Pour into dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: iron skillet chicken
directions: Cut chicken into chunks; flour and fry in lard in iron skillet until done, adding salt and pepper while frying. Remove pieces; drain grease, leaving cracklings. Add can of condensed chicken soup and a little water to thin and simmer chicken for 15 minutes. (May also be cooked in metal skillet.) Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: barley casserole
directions: Brown onion and barley in oleo. Add mushrooms and chicken broth. Bake, covered, 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Take out and add slivered almonds. Bake, uncovered, for 30 more minutes.

title: upside-down ground beef pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Break meat up while cooking. Drain off excess drippings.
Add sauce to meat; cook until thoroughly heated.
Spread mixture over bottom of buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Mix corn muffin mix according to directions. Spread evenly over top of meat mixture. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Test for doneness.
Cool before serving.
Serve warm! Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican combo
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in a large skillet, using a fork to break up meat.
Mix chili powder and hot water; pour over meat mixture.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cheese, beans with juice, salt and pepper.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Be careful not to let burn.

title: cornflakes cookies
directions: Make balls and roll in crushed Corn Flakes.
Add a cherry on top.
You can also put filling between cookies.

title: indian meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pack into a loaf pan, 5 x 9-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix together well.
Add cheese to your liking.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecued butter beans
directions: Simmer together all ingredients, except butter beans, for 5 minutes.
Drain beans and add to sauce.
Cook in oven, covered, for 40 minutes at 375°.
Uncover; stir and bake for 10 minutes.

title: doughnut balls
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and egg.
Melt Crisco; add to the first mixture.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg (which have been sifted together) to the liquid mixture.
Stir only until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon into oil heated to about 375°.
Fry doughnut balls until brown and cooked in the center (about 3 to 4 minutes of frying time).
Remove from oil and drain on crushed absorbent paper.
Roll in powdered sugar.
A family favorite.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and water. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup of Doritos over bottom of crust; put meat mixture over Doritos.
Spread sour cream over meat mixture and cover with cheese.
Add remaining Doritos and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cut like a pie.

title: whole-grain oatmeal pancakes(good for the heart.)
directions: In a small bowl, mix milk and honey until honey is dissolved. Add oatmeal and stir to coat evenly; set aside.
In another bowl, stir together flour and baking powder.
Add oat mixture, egg whites and 3 tablespoons oil.
Stir just until mixed.

title: carrot ring
directions: Pour into greased mold (bottom lined with Wheaties).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in pan of water 1/3 up side of pan.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook oleo, sugar and syrup, boiling for 7 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well and mix over popcorn well.
Put in large pan.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.

title: elephant ears
directions: Mix in order given.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Knead a little (you may need to add more flour); roll out on well floured board into 4 to 5-inch rounds (very thin).
Drop into hot oil (375°) for 10 to 15 seconds.
Carefully turn over with tongs so they don't break apart.
Do other side for 10 to 15 seconds.
Drain on paper towel.
Brush with stick of melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: yummy cinnamon sticks
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl and set aside. Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed with electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add flour, mixing until well blended. Shape dough into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 30 minutes.

title: carrot surprise
directions: Brown onions in butter; mix with bread crumbs, salt, cheese and water.
Place 1 cup carrots in greased 1-quart casserole. Cover with bread crumb mixture.
Arrange remaining carrots in overlapping circles around edge of casserole.
Dot with margarine. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stephen's cookies(wright)
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add soda and salt to flour.
Mix well; add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto Pam sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: slow cooker applesauce
directions: Wash apples.
Remove stems and cut into quarters.
Cook in covered crock-pot 2 to 3 hours or until tender, stirring every hour.
Puree apples.
Measure and return to crock-pot.
For every cup of applesauce, stir in 1/4 cup of sugar or to taste.
Cook on high for 2 more hours, stirring occasionally.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Add salt to egg white and beat stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla. Stir in coconut and corn flakes.
Drop from teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bring mixed vegetables to a boil. Drain. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs and drizzle with 1 cube melted butter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cook until thick; put in clean jars and seal.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Add potatoes and pimiento to thin white sauce.
Heat through. Season to taste.
Serves 6.

title: lynda's ham and potato casserole
directions: Fry ham in drippings until slightly browned.
Place in bottom of well-greased casserole.
Melt butter in same skillet and blend in flour. Add milk gradually and stir over direct heat until sauce boils and thickens a little.
Add sliced potatoes.
Heat to boiling and pour over ham.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour mixture, chopped nuts and chocolate morsels.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: poor man's beef stroganoff
directions: Flour meat and brown.
Add onion and garlic salt and cook until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients except for milk. Simmer 1 hour.
Add small amount of milk and stir before serving.

title: radish dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine. Add celery salt, sauce, radishes and onions; mix together. Chill. Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the ingredients together and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: grandma barbee's forgotten cookies
directions: Make in evening and forget about them until morning.

title: skinny chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients until creamy, adding egg whites last. Fold in chocolate chips and bake on cookie sheet sprayed lightly with Pam for 9 to 11 minutes.
These cookies freeze well and are a great low-fat alternative of fattening chocolate chip cookies. These cookies have 1.9 grams of fat per cookie.

title: stuffed pork chop
directions: Combine bread, onions, celery, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and add to melted butter; pour over bread mixture with enough hot milk or water to moisten thoroughly.
Lay 3 or 4 pork chops in greased baking dish; put stuffing over chops.
Lay the rest of the pork chops on top.
Season meat if desired.
Bake in a moderate oven for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; cool.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
In mixer bowl, beat 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon of the vanilla.
Gradually add 3/4 cup of the sugar.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add dry ingredients; beat until well combined.
Stir in chocolate mixture and nuts. Beat cheese and remaining 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Spread half of the chocolate mixture in greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour cheese mixture over.
Top with remaining chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, jello and coloring.
Add water.
Stir well and heat to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; cool.
Place the strawberries in pie crust.
Pour the cooled mixture over berries.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: honey glaze for ham
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Brush sauce over ham and bake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Combine with beaten eggs, soup, grated cheese and mayonnaise.
Put into well buttered baking dish. Crush Ritz crackers; mix with softened butter.
Put on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add brown sugar.
Add egg and beat thoroughly. Add vanilla. Stir in the dry oatmeal and the nuts. Mix thoroughly.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.

Drop cookie mixture on wax paper from teaspoon, filled about half. Bake in a 350° oven 5 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Lift wax paper off cookie sheet onto wire rack and cool cookies a few minutes before removing from paper. Wax paper will smoke some during the cooking process.
Makes 16 dozen.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken, debone and chop.
Combine all ingredients.

title: party punch
directions: Mix everything together except 7-Up.
Make rings and freeze. Before serving, add 7-Up and frozen punch rings.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package. Cool with cold water and drain. Take very small amount of spaghetti sauce and spread over bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Brown ground beef and mix with spaghetti sauce. Mix 1 1/4 c. mozzarella with ricotta cheese, half the parmesan and romano cheeses and egg. Pepper generously. Layer noodles, beef mixture then cheese mixture, ending with beef mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Uncover and spread rest of cheeses on top ending with provolone. Bake an additional 10-15 minutes or until cheeses are melted. Serve hot with salad and garlic bread. Will serve 6-8.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in an 8-inch square baking dish and set in oven long enough to melt butter, about 2 minutes.
Tilt dish to coat bottom and sides of dish; set aside.
In medium bowl, beat eggs lightly.
Stir in milk; add flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Beat or whisk just until mixture is smooth.
Stir in spinach and cheese.
Pour into prepared dish.

title: scalloped turkey
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine bread cubes and 1 cup cracker crumbs. Stir in broth, beaten eggs, salt, celery, onions, turkey and mushrooms. Spoon mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole pan. In a saucepan, melt butter; brown remaining cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with hands.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: pat's muffins
directions: Sift together flour and sugar. Make a hole in dry mixture and add milk, oil, egg and blackberries (or berry of your choice). Bake at 400° until brown.

title: martha pafford's peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in casserole or baking dish (9 x 13-inch); heat in oven until butter melts.
Mix in bowl the sugar and flour, gradually adding water.
Pour into baking dish.
Spoon peaches evenly on filling.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Warm beer to take the chill off.
Pour it into measuring cup; set aside.
Heat remaining ingredients, except bread.
Stir until thick.
Remove from heat.
Pour in 1/4 cup beer; stir.
Wait 15 minutes.
Do this until all beer is gone.
Dip is ready.
Carve out inside of rye bread.
Cut into chunks for dipping.
Pour dip into bread bowl.

title: beer cheese
directions: Grate cheese and garlic in a food processor. Add remaining ingredients, mixing until thoroughly blended.
The mixture will be soft but will harden in the refrigerator.
It is better if made ahead of time. Serve with crackers, celery sticks or radish roses.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat beef cubes with flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Brown cubes in oil.
Add chosen liquid, bay leaf and cloves/onion.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add more liquid as needed. Remove bay leaf and cloves, add onions, carrots, celery and potatoes.
Cook 30 minutes longer, or until vegetables are tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Serve with chips.
Makes one gallon.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground chuck. Add onions and green pepper. Saute until tender. Add chili powder, tomato soup, sauce and paste. Cook 10 minutes, then add the cheese. Cook until cheese melts. Serve hot.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Put oil into skillet and brown chicken breasts. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix honey and mustard and pour over chicken. Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is done, approximately 25 minutes. Cook rice until done. Pour chicken and honey mustard mixture over rice and serve.

title: chili cheese logs
directions: Mix Velveeta cheese and cream cheese together; add Ranch dressing mix to taste. Separate into 6 small batches. Sprinkle wax paper with chili powder; roll each batch into a log on the wax paper, coating it with chili powder. Makes 6 small logs.

title: easy formal chicken
directions: Place breasts in pan.
Skin up and ends rolled under.
Top each with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Blob sour cream on top.
Sprinkle dry dressing all over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be served with cooked broccoli and sprinkled with sesame seed.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Combine sugar and Karo in pan. Bring to boil.
Then add peanut butter. Stir until creamy. Pour in corn flakes. Drop onto waxed paper by teaspoons.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients, add drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Cube and boil turnips in salted water until tender.
Remove and cool under tap water.
In heavy pan, melt butter (medium heat).
Add onions, celery, bell pepper, garlic, green onions, ham and bacon.
Saute until wilted, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cubed turnips and mix into seasoning mixture.
Fold in parsley and seasoned bread crumbs.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Place turnip mixture in 9 x 12-inch baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly.
This dish freezes well.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar (1/2 cup at a time) and beat.
Add chocolate and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and zucchini. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic cheese roll
directions: In
large
bowl, blend cheeses.
Add all seasonings and mix until
smooth.
Dust
hands with flour and shape into two rolls the
size
of
silver
dollars.
Mix
chili
powder and paprika; spread
on sheet of wax paper.
Roll cheese, flatten ends
and roll
them also.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for
24 hours.
Freezes well.
(For low calorie, use half and half, Velveeta cheese and omit salt.)

title: pierogi(polish dumplings)
directions: Mound flour on board and make holes in center.
Drop in eggs and cut into flour with a knife.
Add salt and water and knead firm.
Let rest 10 minutes in a covered bowl.
Divide dough and roll thin.
Cut large circles.
Place small spoonful of filling on each.
Moisten edges; fold over and press together firmly.
Drop into salted boiling water.
Cook gently about 5 minutes.
Lift out of water and drain well.
When ready to serve, pour melted butter over each or fry in butter until crisp on both sides.

title: savory sour cream spread
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place cottage cheese and eggs in blender. Blend on medium speed for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until smooth.

Add cottage cheese mixture, 1 1/2 cups sour cream and remaining ingredients; beat until smooth. Pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan; place on cookie sheet. Bake 60 to 70 minutes in lower third of oven until top just starts to brown.
Turn oven off; leave pan in oven with door ajar 30 minutes.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/3 cup butter; press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk.
Fold in half of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix 3 1/2 cups milk and pudding.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill overnight.
Spread the rest of Cool Whip over pudding and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Soak apricots in cold water about 4 hours.
Drain, reserve water and up to 1 pint.
Heat oil and butter in pan and fry chicken on both sides.
Transfer to casserole dish.
Fry onions about 3 minutes, turn down heat and stir in flour.
Add apricot liquid stirring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour sauce over chicken, cover and cook at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Remove garni before serving.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate dipped shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls, using one slightly rounded teaspoonful for each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets; cool.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water, semi-sweet morsels and shortening.
Dip each cookie halfway into melted chocolate.
Shake off excess, roll in chopped nuts, if desired.
Chill in refrigerator on waxed paper lined cookie sheets about 30 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen (1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: guacamole
directions: Smash avocados with a fork.
Smash up whole tomatoes.
Do not use juice from tomatoes.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Add cilantro to taste.
Squeeze lemon juice over entire mixture.
(Put an avocado seed in to keep mixture from turning brown.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Smooth mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and slivered almonds.
Cook for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over cake as soon as it is removed from the oven.
Let cool completely.
Add Cool Whip and then fresh frozen coconut.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Thinly slice chilled cookie dough and arrange slices closely together on ungreased pizza pan.
Let dough stand a few minutes to soften, then press together to cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes; cool.
Slice the fruit and dip apples in pineapple juice.
Mix cream cheese with honey.
Spread cheese on cooled cookie crust.
Arrange the fruit on top.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix all together and store in a covered dish overnight, or a few hrs. I add sliced onions and another jar of marinated artichokes.
Recipe is good with any combination of fresh vegetables you like.
Mushrooms and onions are better added the day you serve.
Lasts several days.
Drain and reserve marinade when serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon onto hot griddle or pan. Flip over to finish cooking.
Great with soup or salad or eat cold.

title: egg and swiss cheese salad
directions: Toss eggs and cheese together lightly in a bowl. In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients; pour over egg-cheese mixture and toss gently. Serve on dark or white bread, crisp lettuce, spinach or crackers. Serves 6.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Certo.
Bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove foam from top. Add Certo and red or green food coloring.
Serve over cream cheese with snack crackers.
Good at Christmas.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine chicken or turkey, almonds, onions, celery, lemon juice, salt and mayonnaise.
Put in flat baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: beef-tomato-potato casserole
directions: Arrange layer of potatoes in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole; season with salt and pepper. Put ground beef on top of potatoes; pour tomatoes over beef. Sprinkle with oregano and spread with slices of onion. Cover and bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Remove lid and brown.

title: coconut millet pudding
directions: In large saucepan, heat milk slowly until scalded. Add millet, honey, coconut, salt and vanilla.
Pour into an oiled oven casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until the millet is tender.
Serve hot or chilled with whipping cream and preserves.
Serves 6.

title: easy caramel cake
directions: Melt sugar and margarine over low heat.
Add milk.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat until cool and thick.
Ice cake.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel and cut apples into cubes.
Blend 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle and mix over apples.
Set aside.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly, then add eggs and milk, blending well.
With finger over the small hole in funnel, place about 3/4 cup batter in funnel.
Holding funnel over hot shortening, remove finger from small funnel hole.
Slowly move the funnel in rings until all the batter has run out.
When cakes float to the surface and are lightly brown, flip over with a fork, allowing both sides to brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm or top with your favorite preserves.
The batter should be a little thicker than pancake batter so that it will run out of the funnel evenly.
These cakes can be made in a cast-iron skillet or a deep fryer.

title: citrus and pineapple compote
directions: In a bowl, combine the grapefruit sections, the orange slices and the pineapple chunks.
In a small saucepan, combine the reserved juices, the sherry, the honey and a pinch of salt and simmer the mixture, stirring, for one minute.
Pour the mixture over fruit and toss compote gently.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: onion mashed potatoes
directions: Combine everything but onion rings and beat until blended. Beat at high speed until creamy and smooth.
Layer with onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine Crisco and butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Alternately add flour and milk.
Then add vanilla. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts; layer in bottom of pan (take off bone). Mix cream of chicken soup and 1 carton sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Crush the Ritz crackers and pour over.
Pour melted butter on top.
Cook about 25 or 30 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches, saving the syrup.
Arrange in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Combine 1/4 cup peach syrup, lemon juice and lemon rind and pour over peaches.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add shortening, egg and 1/3 cup reserved syrup until moistened. Spread over peaches and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla, pineapple and zucchini; mix well.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda and add to first mixture, then add nuts; mix well.
Put in 2 greased and floured bread tins.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes (or until done) at 325°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: This is a recipe to use for a "fun" get together.
Tell the guests
to follow the instructions on the cards placed at each item and that the name "pile-up" means that each succeeding item is to be piled on top of the preceding item.

title: quick and easy tuna patties
directions: Drain tuna.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Form into patties and fry in melted shortening (or oil) until golden brown (approximately 5 minutes).

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs over oleo and press.
Layer chocolate chips, coconut and nuts. Drizzle all over top can Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until top browns.

title: mushroom soup
directions: In butter, in saucepan, saute mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Add soup and dill.
Gradually stir in water; heat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix everything except onion rings and cheese.
Put into 3-quart casserole.
Cover with cheese with onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rey's salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor and pulse several times until vegetables are chopped well.

title: hors d'asphalt
directions: Saute venison, bunny and squirrels in rattlesnake grease. (Warning: Use only cast-iron frypan.

Teflon and other nonstick coatings may impart a flavor to the dish which may disrupt the subtleness of the various ingredients and their delicate bouquet.) Take pinto beans and remove bugs, sticks, lizards, etc., and add raw housecat and frog.
Simmer bean-cat-frog mixture for several hours over low heat (do not boil; add water as necessary).
After simmering beans, add jalapenos.
(Here, improvisation is allowed. Feel free to add extra tidbits for flavoring: e.g., corncobs, clamshells, fish scales, flies, shoe laces, etc.
Your guests will be pleasantly amused.)
Serve bean mixture and meat delectables in separate dishes.
(Important to protect the distinct and unique characters of each.)
Serve only on finest china (silver service also recommended).
Garnish with chicory or yarrow for effect.
A hearty lambrusco (or MD 20/20) is a good choice.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken francese
directions: Lightly pound chicken (shiny side down).
Dip in flour to coat, then in eggs.
Cook in hot oil until golden brown on both sides. Drain oil from pan and add butter, lemon juice, garlic and mushrooms to pan.
Cook over medium heat until chicken is cooked through and mushrooms are soft, but not soggy (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Arrange on platter.
Pour liquid from pan over chicken. Sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: In a bowl, alternate the cabbage with the onion rings.
Cover with 3/4 cup sugar and permit to stand awhile.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, 1 tablespoon sugar, salt, celery seed and dry mustard. Add the oil.
Heat again.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and allow to stand 2 hours or more before stirring.
This keeps very well in the refrigerator for some time.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until done, then drain thoroughly.
In a 2-quart baking dish, put layers of macaroni and layers of cheese alternately until both are used.
Beat together eggs, milk
and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Pour egg-milk mixture over macaroni and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until egg mixture is set.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar and butter. Gradually blend in milk. In mixing bowl, blend sugar, cornstarch and salt. Blend in eggs and vanilla. Add this mixture to chocolate mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Combine coconut and pecans and top pie with mixture. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until puffed up and browned. Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Stir in egg, salt, pepper, onion and pimento.
Add cracker crumbs and mix lightly.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter, mixed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown and crusty on top.

title: chocolate chip cookie roll
directions: Cream together oleo, peanut butter and sugars.
Mix in egg. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough.
Melt 3/4 cup chocolate chips.
Roll out dough and spread with melted chocolate. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Roll up dough; slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Crust:
Combine whole wheat flour, 2/3 cup cheese, almonds, salt and paprika in a bowl.
Stir in oil.
Set aside 1/2 cup crust.
Press remaining crust into 9-inch quiche dish or pie pan. Bake crust in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove crust and reduce oven to 325°.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix together except the chopped nuts; form into a ball and roll in the chopped nuts.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: In a bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and potatoes.
Measure flour.
Mix in flour with hands until dough is easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place greased side up in greased bowl.
Place wax paper over dough.
Cover with a damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator about 2 hours or overnight.
Before baking, shape dough in cloverleaf rolls.
Cover and let rise until double, about 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken sotanghon(asian transparent noodles)*
directions: Saute garlic in hot oil until slightly brown. Add onion and stir for 1 minute. Add chicken cubes and saute for 5 minutes or until chicken turns light brown. Add mushrooms to chicken mixture and stir-fry for 1 minute, then add the achuete juice. Season with patis, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth and cook to boiling. Add drained sotanghon and cook for 10 minutes more or until sotanghon is tender. Garnish with green onions. Serves 8.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Combine
cake mix with cocoa.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, red food coloring, melted margarine and eggs. Blend well with electric mixer.
Add
soda
and
vinegar
together.
Add
to mixture. Beat for 5 minutes or until smooth. Grease and flour pans. Pour batter
in pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Make a Cream Cheese Icing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well, then add sugar, oil, squash and vanilla and mix well.
Next, add dry ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Cook and stir meat and onions in oil in large skillet over medium heat until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Pour off oil.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Boil together water and sugar, then add cherry filling.
Bring to a boil.
Add 6 ounces jello; stir until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple, lemon juice, Coke and walnuts.
Set and chill.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and molasses together.
Stir the hot water and soda until dissolved.
Mix flour and ginger, then add everything together to make a thick dough.
Drop by spoonful into a dish of sugar.
When coated with sugar, roll into a ball. Flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.

title: the tropic "fruit cup"
directions: Combine contents of cans into bowl.
Stir bananas into fruit. Stir and chill.
Enjoy!

title: summer pasta
directions: Mix ingredients except pasta.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature, covered.
Toss over cooked pasta.
Serve immediately with grated Parmesan cheese.
(Mix can be made the day before.)

title: fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch thick slices; separate into rings. Combine Bisquick, salt and milk.
Coat onions in Bisquick batter. Heat cooking oil in deep fat fryer.
Fry onion rings in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain thoroughly on paper towels.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix and bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° until brown, about 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hamburg mushroom bake
directions: Mix beef with milk.
Form into 4 patties and place in bottom of casserole.
Microwave for 5 minutes.
Drain liquid.
Cover beef with mushroom soup.
Microwave for 3 or so minutes.
Sprinkle onions on top of casserole.
Microwave for 1 minute.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save.
Combine 3 tablespoons of pineapple juice, sugar and flour to make paste.
Stir in rest of juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into greased 1 quart casserole.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until slightly brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Put sugar on rhubarb and let stand for a few hours. Boil rhubarb until tender. Take off stove and add jello.

title: hot cheese - one pan dish
directions: Cook beef and green chilies until meat is done.
Drain all grease off.
Melt cheese in double boiler with evaporated milk. Cook egg noodles.
Put all ingredients in a large pan and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter cheese balls
directions: Combine
peanut butter, cream cheese, sugar and milk in a medium
mixing
bowl.
Beat
on medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add more milk, if needed, for a creamier texture. Shape
mixture
into a ball; roll in peanuts.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with apple wedges or whole wheat crackers.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil.
Add Ritz crackers. Do not stir; leave crackers whole.
Let boil 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put top crust on and bake 10 minutes at 425° and then 25 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan harvest cake
directions: Set butter out to soften.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Grease bottom of 10-inch tube pan.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks well.
Beat whites until stiff.
Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add yolks, mixing well.
Combine milk, vanilla and coffee.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in pecans and egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream or icing.

title: crab casserole
directions: Break crabmeat into chunks.
Mix with all the rest of the ingredients except buttered soft bread crumbs.
Pile into greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until bubbly.
Can be garnished with sliced olives.
Serves 6.

title: yogurt and spinach dip
directions: Steam the spinach in a steamer for 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat and mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs and pecans. Place remaining ingredients in a bowl and beat well. Pour in dry ingredients.
Mix well. Form dough into balls. Roll balls into powdered sugar and pecans.

title: elegant wine mushrooms
directions: Clean the mushrooms, leaving the stems on.
Combine all other ingredients in a large saucepan and add the mushrooms.
Bring to a slow boil on medium heat and then reduce to a simmer.
Cook 5 hours with pot covered, stirring now and then.
Remove cover and cook another 3 to 5 hours, until the liquid barely covers the mushrooms.

title: winter salad bake
directions: Make white sauce adding dry mustard, salt and pepper and cooking 1 minute.
Remove from heat and blend in salad dressing. Fold in 1/2 potatoes, onion and wieners.
Decorate with slices of wieners and bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup margarine, eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour into buttered baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Top with brown sugar, flour, nuts and 1/3 cup margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple mallow crisp
directions: Place apples, raisins and water in 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: good and easy cornbread
directions: You will also need one nonstick baking pan (7 x 11) or iron skillet.

title: cinnamon chocolate milk shake
directions: In blender, process ingredients.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan. Cook over medium heat. Stir until thickens and boil for 1 minute.
